fields.name: MODE
fields.desc: This bits decides which one operation mode will be used. 3'd0: AES-EN-128, 3'd1: AES-EN-192, 3'd2: AES-EN-256, 3'd4: AES-DE-128, 3'd5: AES-DE-192, 3'd6: AES-DE-256.

fields.name: ENDIAN
fields.desc: endian. [1:0] key endian, [3:2] text_in endian or in_stream endian,  [5:4] text_out endian or out_stream endian

fields.name: TRIGGER
fields.desc: Set this bit to start AES calculation.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: Those bits shows AES status. For typical AES, 0: idle, 1: busy. For DMA-AES, 0: idle, 1: busy, 2: calculation_done.

1611169872.name: IV_MEM[%s]
1611169872.desc: The memory that stores initialization vector

1611169888.name: H_MEM[%s]
1611169888.desc: The memory that stores GCM hash subkey

fields.name: DMA_ENABLE
fields.desc: 1'b0: typical AES working mode, 1'b1: DMA-AES working mode.

fields.name: BLOCK_MODE
fields.desc: Those bits decides which block mode will be used. 0x0: ECB, 0x1: CBC, 0x2: OFB, 0x3: CTR, 0x4: CFB-8, 0x5: CFB-128, 0x6: GCM, 0x7: reserved.

fields.name: BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: Those bits stores the number of Plaintext/ciphertext block.

fields.name: INC_SEL
fields.desc: This bit decides the standard incrementing function. 0: INC32. 1: INC128.

1611169952.name: AAD_BLOCK_NUM
1611169952.desc: Additional Authential Data block number register

fields.name: AAD_BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: Those bits stores the number of AAD block.

fields.name: REMAINDER_BIT_NUM
fields.desc: Those bits stores the number of remainder bit.

fields.name: CONTINUE
fields.desc: Set this bit to continue GCM operation.

fields.name: INT_CLEAR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the AES interrupt.

fields.name: INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable interrupt that occurs when DMA-AES calculation is done.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This bits stores the version information of AES.

fields.name: DMA_EXIT
fields.desc: Set this register to leave calculation done stage. Recommend to use it after software finishes reading DMA's output buffer.

fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the second section of prelock on L1-Cache, which should be used together with L1_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE_REG

1611432068.name: L1_DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT_SIZE
1611432068.desc: L1  Cache prelock section size configure register

fields.name: L1_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the first section of prelock on L1-Cache, which should be used together with L1_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR_REG

fields.name: L1_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the second section of prelock on L1-Cache, which should be used together with L1_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR_REG

fields.name: CACHE_LOCK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable lock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after lock operation done

fields.name: CACHE_UNLOCK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable unlock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after unlock operation done

fields.name: CACHE_LOCK_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether unlock/lock operation is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

fields.name: CACHE_LOCK_RGID
fields.desc: The bit is used to set  the gid of cache lock/unlock.

fields.name: CACHE_LOCK_MAP
fields.desc: Those bits are used to indicate which caches in the two-level cache structure will apply this lock/unlock operation. [4]: L1-Cache

fields.name: CACHE_LOCK_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the lock/unlock operation, which should be used together with CACHE_LOCK_SIZE_REG

fields.name: CACHE_LOCK_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the lock/unlock operation, which should be used together with CACHE_LOCK_ADDR_REG

fields.name: CACHE_INVALIDATE_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable invalidate operation. It will be cleared by hardware after invalidate operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (clean_ena, writeback_ena, writeback_invalidate_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

fields.name: CACHE_CLEAN_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable clean operation. It will be cleared by hardware after clean operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (invalidate_ena, writeback_ena, writeback_invalidate_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

fields.name: CACHE_WRITEBACK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable writeback operation. It will be cleared by hardware after writeback operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (invalidate_ena, clean_ena, writeback_invalidate_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

fields.name: CACHE_WRITEBACK_INVALIDATE_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable writeback-invalidate operation. It will be cleared by hardware after writeback-invalidate operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (invalidate_ena, clean_ena, writeback_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

fields.name: CACHE_SYNC_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether sync operation (invalidate, clean, writeback, writeback_invalidate) is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

fields.name: CACHE_SYNC_RGID
fields.desc: The bit is used to set  the gid of cache sync operation (invalidate, clean, writeback, writeback_invalidate)

fields.name: CACHE_SYNC_MAP
fields.desc: Those bits are used to indicate which caches in the two-level cache structure will apply the sync operation.  [4]: L1-Cache

fields.name: CACHE_SYNC_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the sync operation, which should be used together with CACHE_SYNC_SIZE_REG

fields.name: CACHE_SYNC_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the sync operation, which should be used together with CACHE_SYNC_ADDR_REG

fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache0 preload-operation is done.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_PLD_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache1 preload-operation is done.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_PLD_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_CACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-Cache preload-operation is done.

fields.name: CACHE_SYNC_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when Cache sync-operation is done.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L1-ICache0 preload-operation error.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L1-ICache1 preload-operation error.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_CACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L1-Cache preload-operation error.

fields.name: CACHE_SYNC_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of Cache sync-operation error.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L1-ICache0.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L1-ICache1.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_CACHE_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L1-Cache.

fields.name: CACHE_SYNC_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: The values 0-2 are available which means sync map, command conflict and size are error in Cache System.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L1-ICache0. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L1-ICache1. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_CACHE_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L1-Cache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_PLD_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L1-ICache0. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_PLD_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L1-ICache1. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_PLD_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_CACHE_PLD_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L1-Cache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

1611432512.name: L1_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_BUF_CLR_CTRL
1611432512.desc: Cache Autoload buffer clear control register

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L1-ICache0. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L1-ICache0. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L1-ICache0.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L1-ICache1. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L1-ICache1. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L1-ICache1.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_CACHE_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L1-Cache. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L1-Cache. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L1-Cache.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l1 icache0 where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l1 icache1 where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_CACHE_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l1 cache where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

1611432520.name: L1_CACHE_OBJECT_CTRL
1611432520.desc: Cache Tag and Data memory Object control register

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_TAG_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L1-ICache0 tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_TAG_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L1-ICache1 tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_TAG_OBJECT
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_TAG_OBJECT
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_CACHE_TAG_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L1-Cache tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_MEM_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L1-ICache0 data memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_MEM_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L1-ICache1 data memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_MEM_OBJECT
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_MEM_OBJECT
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_CACHE_MEM_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L1-Cache data memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

1611432524.name: L1_CACHE_WAY_OBJECT
1611432524.desc: Cache Tag and Data memory way register

fields.name: L1_CACHE_WAY_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bits to select which way of the tag-object will be accessed. 0: way0, 1: way1, 2: way2, 3: way3, ?, 7: way7.

fields.name: L1_CACHE_VADDR
fields.desc: Those bits stores the virtual address which will decide where inside the specified tag memory object will be accessed.

fields.name: L1_CACHE_DEBUG_BUS
fields.desc: This is a constant place where we can write data to or read data from the tag/data memory on the specified cache.

1611432536.name: LEVEL_SPLIT0
1611432536.desc: USED TO SPLIT L1 CACHE AND L2 CACHE

fields.name: LEVEL_SPLIT0
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L2_CACHE_SHUT_DMA
fields.desc: The bit is used to disable DMA access L2-Cache, 0: enable, 1: disable

fields.name: L2_CACHE_UNDEF_OP
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: BYPASS_L2_CACHE_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable bypass L2-Cache. 0: disable bypass, 1: enable bypass.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_128K

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_256K

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_512K
fields.desc: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 512k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_1024K
fields.desc: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 1024k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_2048K
fields.desc: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 2048k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_4096K

1611432552.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_CONF
1611432552.desc: L2 Cache BlockSize mode configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_8
fields.desc: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 8 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_16
fields.desc: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 16 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_32
fields.desc: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 32 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_64

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_128
fields.desc: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 128 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_256
fields.desc: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 256 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_WRAP
fields.desc: Set this bit as 1 to enable L2-Cache wrap around mode.

1611432560.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_POWER_CTRL
1611432560.desc: Cache tag memory power control register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: The bit is used to close clock gating of  L2-Cache tag memory. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: The bit is used to power L2-Cache tag memory down. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power down

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: The bit is used to power L2-Cache tag memory up. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power up

1611432564.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_POWER_CTRL
1611432564.desc: Cache data memory power control register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: The bit is used to close clock gating of  L2-Cache data memory. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: The bit is used to power L2-Cache data memory down. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power down

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: The bit is used to power L2-Cache data memory up. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power up

fields.name: L2_CACHE_FREEZE_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable freeze operation on L2-Cache. It can be cleared by software.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_FREEZE_MODE
fields.desc: The bit is used to configure mode of freeze operation L2-Cache. 0: a miss-access will not stuck. 1: a miss-access will stuck.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_FREEZE_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether freeze operation on L2-Cache is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

1611432572.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_ACS_CONF
1611432572.desc: Cache data memory access configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_RD_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable config-bus read L2-Cache data memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_WR_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable config-bus write L2-Cache data memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

1611432576.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_ACS_CONF
1611432576.desc: Cache tag memory access configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_RD_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable config-bus read L2-Cache tag memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_WR_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable config-bus write L2-Cache tag memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable the first section of prelock function on L2-Cache.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable the second section of prelock function on L2-Cache.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_RGID
fields.desc: The bit is used to set  the gid of l2 cache prelock.

1611432584.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR
1611432584.desc: L2 Cache prelock section0 address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the first section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_SIZE_REG

1611432588.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR
1611432588.desc: L2 Cache prelock section1 address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the second section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE_REG

1611432592.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT_SIZE
1611432592.desc: L2 Cache prelock section size configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the first section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR_REG

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the second section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR_REG

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable preload operation on L2-Cache. It will be cleared by hardware automatically after preload operation is done.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether preload operation is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ORDER
fields.desc: The bit is used to configure the direction of preload operation. 0: ascending, 1: descending.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_RGID
fields.desc: The bit is used to set  the gid of l2 cache preload.

1611432600.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR
1611432600.desc: L2 Cache preload address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of preload on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE_REG

1611432604.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE
1611432604.desc: L2 Cache preload size configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the first section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR_REG

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable and disable autoload operation on L2-Cache.  1: enable, 0: disable.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether autoload operation on L2-Cache is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_ORDER
fields.desc: The bit is used to configure the direction of autoload operation on L2-Cache. 0: ascending. 1: descending.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_TRIGGER_MODE
fields.desc: The field is used to configure trigger mode of autoload operation on L2-Cache. 0/3: miss-trigger, 1: hit-trigger, 2: miss-hit-trigger.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable the first section for autoload operation on L2-Cache.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable the second section for autoload operation on L2-Cache.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable the third section for autoload operation on L2-Cache.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable the fourth section for autoload operation on L2-Cache.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_RGID
fields.desc: The bit is used to set  the gid of l2 cache autoload.

1611432612.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ADDR
1611432612.desc: L2 Cache autoload section 0 address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the first section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_SIZE and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ENA.

1611432616.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_SIZE
1611432616.desc: L2 Cache autoload section 0 size configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the first section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ADDR and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ENA.

1611432620.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ADDR
1611432620.desc: L2 Cache autoload section 1 address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the second section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_SIZE and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ENA.

1611432624.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_SIZE

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the second section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ADDR and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ENA.

1611432628.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ADDR
1611432628.desc: L2 Cache autoload section 2 address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the third section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_SIZE and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ENA.

1611432632.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_SIZE
1611432632.desc: L2 Cache autoload section 2 size configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the third section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ADDR and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ENA.

1611432636.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ADDR
1611432636.desc: L2 Cache autoload section 3 address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the fourth section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_SIZE and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ENA.

1611432640.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_SIZE
1611432640.desc: L2 Cache autoload section 3 size configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the fourth section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ADDR and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ENA.

1610629120.name: SCL_LOW_PERIOD
1610629120.desc:
Configures the low level width of the SCL
Clock

fields.name: SCL_LOW_PERIOD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SCL remains low in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

fields.name: SDA_FORCE_OUT
fields.desc: 1: direct output, 0: open drain output.

fields.name: SCL_FORCE_OUT
fields.desc: 1: direct output, 0: open drain output.

fields.name: SAMPLE_SCL_LEVEL
fields.desc:
This register is used to select the sample mode.
1: sample SDA data on the SCL low level.
0: sample SDA data on the SCL high level.

fields.name: RX_FULL_ACK_LEVEL
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the ACK value that need to sent by master when the rx_fifo_cnt has reached the threshold.

fields.name: MS_MODE
fields.desc:
Set this bit to configure the module as an I2C Master. Clear this bit to configure the
module as an I2C Slave.

fields.name: TRANS_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start sending the data in txfifo.

fields.name: TX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
This bit is used to control the sending mode for data needing to be sent. 
1: send data from the least significant bit,
0: send data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: RX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
This bit is used to control the storage mode for received data.
1: receive data from the least significant bit,
0: receive data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: ARBITRATION_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for arbitration_lost.

fields.name: FSM_RST
fields.desc: This register is used to reset the scl FMS.

fields.name: CONF_UPGATE
fields.desc: synchronization bit

fields.name: SLV_TX_AUTO_START_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for slave to send data automatically

fields.name: ADDR_10BIT_RW_CHECK_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit to check if the r/w bit of 10bit addressing consists with I2C protocol

fields.name: ADDR_BROADCASTING_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit to support the 7bit general call function.

fields.name: RESP_REC
fields.desc: The received ACK value in master mode or slave mode. 0: ACK, 1: NACK.

fields.name: SLAVE_RW
fields.desc: When in slave mode, 1: master reads from slave, 0: master writes to slave.

fields.name: ARB_LOST
fields.desc: When the I2C controller loses control of SCL line, this register changes to 1.

fields.name: BUS_BUSY
fields.desc: 1: the I2C bus is busy transferring data, 0: the I2C bus is in idle state.

fields.name: SLAVE_ADDRESSED
fields.desc:
When configured as an I2C Slave, and the address sent by the master is
equal to the address of the slave, then this bit will be of high level.

fields.name: RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: This field represents the amount of data needed to be sent.

fields.name: STRETCH_CAUSE
fields.desc: The cause of stretching SCL low in slave mode. 0:  stretching SCL low at the beginning of I2C read data state. 1: stretching SCL low when I2C Tx FIFO is empty in slave mode. 2: stretching SCL low when I2C Rx FIFO is full in slave mode.

fields.name: TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: This field stores the amount of received data in RAM.

fields.name: SCL_MAIN_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
This field indicates the states of the I2C module state machine. 
0: Idle, 1: Address shift, 2: ACK address, 3: Rx data, 4: Tx data, 5: Send ACK, 6: Wait ACK

fields.name: SCL_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
This field indicates the states of the state machine used to produce SCL.
0: Idle, 1: Start, 2: Negative edge, 3: Low, 4: Positive edge, 5: High, 6: Stop

1610629168.desc: Configures the hold time after a negative SCL edge.

This register is used to configure the time to hold the data after the negative
edge of SCL, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629172.name: SDA_SAMPLE
1610629172.desc: Configures the sample time after a positive SCL edge.

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SDA is sampled, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629176.desc: Configures the high level width of SCL

fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SCL remains high in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

fields.name: SCL_WAIT_HIGH_PERIOD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for the SCL_FSM's waiting period for SCL high level in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629184.name: SCL_START_HOLD
1610629184.desc: Configures the delay between the SDA and SCL negative edge for a start condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time between the negative edge
of SDA and the negative edge of SCL for a START condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629188.name: SCL_RSTART_SETUP
1610629188.desc:
Configures the delay between the positive
edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time between the positive
edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA for a RESTART condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

1610629192.name: SCL_STOP_HOLD
1610629192.desc:
Configures the delay after the SCL clock
edge for a stop condition

fields.name: TIME

This register is used to configure the delay after the STOP condition,

1610629196.name: SCL_STOP_SETUP
1610629196.desc:

fields.name: TIME

This register is used to configure the time between the positive edge

1610629200.name: FILTER_CFG
1610629200.desc: SCL and SDA filter configuration register

fields.name: SCL_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc:
When a pulse on the SCL input has smaller width than this register value
in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

fields.name: SDA_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc:
When a pulse on the SDA input has smaller width than this register value
in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

fields.name: SCL_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the filter enable bit for SCL.

fields.name: SDA_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the filter enable bit for SDA.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: the integral part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_A
fields.desc: the numerator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_B
fields.desc: the denominator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

fields.name: SCLK_SEL
fields.desc: The clock selection for i2c module:0-XTAL,1-CLK_8MHz.

fields.name: SCLK_ACTIVE
fields.desc: The clock switch for i2c module

fields.name: COMMAND
fields.desc:
This is the content of command 0. It consists of three parts: 
op_code is the command, 0: RSTART, 1: WRITE, 2: READ, 3: STOP, 4: END.
Byte_num represents the number of bytes that need to be sent or received.
ack_check_en, ack_exp and ack are used to control the ACK bit. See I2C cmd structure for more
Information.

fields.name: COMMAND_DONE
fields.desc:
When command 0 is done in I2C Master mode, this bit changes to high
level.

fields.name: SCL_ST_TO_I2C
fields.desc: The threshold value of SCL_FSM state unchanged period. It should be o more than 23

1610629244.name: SCL_MAIN_ST_TIME_OUT
1610629244.desc: SCL main status time out register

fields.name: SCL_MAIN_ST_TO_I2C
fields.desc: The threshold value of SCL_MAIN_FSM state unchanged period.nIt should be o more than 23

fields.name: SCL_RST_SLV_EN
fields.desc: When I2C master is IDLE, set this bit to send out SCL pulses. The number of pulses equals to reg_scl_rst_slv_num[4:0].

fields.name: SCL_RST_SLV_NUM
fields.desc: Configure the pulses of SCL generated in I2C master mode. Valid when reg_scl_rst_slv_en is 1.

fields.name: SCL_PD_EN
fields.desc: The power down enable bit for the I2C output SCL line. 1: Power down. 0: Not power down. Set reg_scl_force_out and reg_scl_pd_en to 1 to stretch SCL low.

fields.name: SDA_PD_EN
fields.desc: The power down enable bit for the I2C output SDA line. 1: Power down. 0: Not power down. Set reg_sda_force_out and reg_sda_pd_en to 1 to stretch SDA low.

1610629252.name: SCL_STRETCH_CONF
1610629252.desc: Set SCL stretch of I2C slave

fields.name: STRETCH_PROTECT_NUM
fields.desc: Configure the period of I2C slave stretching SCL line.

fields.name: SLAVE_SCL_STRETCH_EN
fields.desc: The enable bit for slave SCL stretch function. 1: Enable. 0: Disable. The SCL output line will be stretched low when reg_slave_scl_stretch_en is 1 and stretch event happens. The stretch cause can be seen in reg_stretch_cause.

fields.name: SLAVE_SCL_STRETCH_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the I2C slave SCL stretch function.

fields.name: SLAVE_BYTE_ACK_CTL_EN
fields.desc: The enable bit for slave to control ACK level function.

fields.name: SLAVE_BYTE_ACK_LVL
fields.desc: Set the ACK level when slave controlling ACK level function enables.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the the version register.

fields.desc: Set this bit to reset Rx AFIFO

fields.name: RX_START

fields.name: RX_SLAVE_MOD
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable slave receiver mode

fields.name: RX_MONO
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver  in mono mode

fields.name: RX_BIG_ENDIAN
fields.desc: I2S Rx byte endian, 1: low addr value to high addr. 0: low addr with low addr value.

fields.name: RX_UPDATE
fields.desc: Set 1 to update I2S RX registers from APB clock domain to I2S RX clock domain. This bit will be cleared by hardware after update register done.

fields.name: RX_MONO_FST_VLD
fields.desc: 1: The first channel data value is valid in I2S RX mono mode.   0: The second channel data value is valid in I2S RX mono mode.

fields.name: RX_PCM_CONF
fields.desc: I2S RX compress/decompress configuration bit. & 0 (atol): A-Law decompress, 1 (ltoa) : A-Law compress, 2 (utol) : u-Law decompress, 3 (ltou) : u-Law compress. &

fields.name: RX_PCM_BYPASS
fields.desc: Set this bit to bypass Compress/Decompress module for received data.

fields.name: RX_STOP_MODE
fields.desc: 0  : I2S Rx only stop when reg_rx_start is cleared.   1: Stop when reg_rx_start is 0 or in_suc_eof is 1.   2:  Stop I2S RX when reg_rx_start is 0 or RX FIFO is full.

fields.name: RX_LEFT_ALIGN
fields.desc: 1: I2S RX left alignment mode. 0: I2S RX right alignment mode.

fields.name: RX_24_FILL_EN
fields.desc: 1: store 24 channel bits to 32 bits. 0:store 24 channel bits to 24 bits.

fields.name: RX_WS_IDLE_POL
fields.desc: 0: WS should be 0 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 1in right channel.  1: WS should be 1 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 0in right channel.

fields.name: RX_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: I2S Rx bit endian. 1:small endian, the LSB is received first. 0:big endian, the MSB is received first.

fields.name: RX_TDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S TDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: RX_PDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S PDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: TX_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset transmitter

fields.name: TX_FIFO_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset Tx AFIFO

fields.name: TX_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start transmitting data

fields.name: TX_SLAVE_MOD
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable slave transmitter mode

fields.name: TX_MONO
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable transmitter in mono mode

fields.name: TX_CHAN_EQUAL
fields.desc: 1: The value of Left channel data is equal to the value of right channel data in I2S TX mono mode or TDM channel select mode. 0: The invalid channel data is reg_i2s_single_data in I2S TX mono mode or TDM channel select mode.

fields.name: TX_BIG_ENDIAN
fields.desc: I2S Tx byte endian, 1: low addr value to high addr.  0: low addr with low addr value.

fields.name: TX_UPDATE
fields.desc: Set 1 to update I2S TX registers from APB clock domain to I2S TX clock domain. This bit will be cleared by hardware after update register done.

fields.name: TX_MONO_FST_VLD
fields.desc: 1: The first channel data value is valid in I2S TX mono mode.   0: The second channel data value is valid in I2S TX mono mode.

fields.name: TX_PCM_CONF
fields.desc: I2S TX compress/decompress configuration bit. & 0 (atol): A-Law decompress, 1 (ltoa) : A-Law compress, 2 (utol) : u-Law decompress, 3 (ltou) : u-Law compress. &

fields.name: TX_PCM_BYPASS
fields.desc: Set this bit to bypass  Compress/Decompress module for transmitted data.

fields.name: TX_STOP_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop disable output BCK signal and WS signal when tx FIFO is emtpy

fields.name: TX_LEFT_ALIGN
fields.desc: 1: I2S TX left alignment mode. 0: I2S TX right alignment mode.

fields.name: TX_24_FILL_EN
fields.desc: 1: Sent 32 bits in 24 channel bits mode. 0: Sent 24 bits in 24 channel bits mode

fields.name: TX_WS_IDLE_POL
fields.desc: 0: WS should be 0 when sending left channel data, and WS is 1in right channel.  1: WS should be 1 when sending left channel data, and WS is 0in right channel.

fields.name: TX_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: I2S Tx bit endian. 1:small endian, the LSB is sent first. 0:big endian, the MSB is sent first.

fields.name: TX_TDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S TDM Tx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: TX_PDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S PDM Tx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: TX_CHAN_MOD
fields.desc: I2S transmitter channel mode configuration bits.

fields.name: SIG_LOOPBACK
fields.desc: Enable signal loop back mode with transmitter module and receiver module sharing the same WS and BCK signals.

fields.name: RX_TDM_WS_WIDTH
fields.desc: The width of rx_ws_out in TDM mode is (I2S_RX_TDM_WS_WIDTH[6:0] +1) * T_bck

fields.name: RX_BCK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Bit clock configuration bits in receiver mode.

fields.name: RX_BITS_MOD
fields.desc: Set the bits to configure the valid data bit length of I2S receiver channel. 7: all the valid channel data is in 8-bit-mode. 15: all the valid channel data is in 16-bit-mode. 23: all the valid channel data is in 24-bit-mode. 31:all the valid channel data is in 32-bit-mode.

fields.name: RX_HALF_SAMPLE_BITS
fields.desc: I2S Rx half sample bits -1.

fields.name: RX_TDM_CHAN_BITS
fields.desc: The Rx bit number for each channel minus 1in TDM mode.

fields.name: RX_MSB_SHIFT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver in Phillips standard mode

fields.name: TX_TDM_WS_WIDTH
fields.desc: The width of tx_ws_out in TDM mode is (I2S_TX_TDM_WS_WIDTH[6:0] +1) * T_bck

fields.name: TX_BCK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Bit clock configuration bits in transmitter mode.

fields.name: TX_BITS_MOD
fields.desc: Set the bits to configure the valid data bit length of I2S transmitter channel. 7: all the valid channel data is in 8-bit-mode. 15: all the valid channel data is in 16-bit-mode. 23: all the valid channel data is in 24-bit-mode. 31:all the valid channel data is in 32-bit-mode.

fields.name: TX_HALF_SAMPLE_BITS
fields.desc: I2S Tx half sample bits -1.

fields.name: TX_TDM_CHAN_BITS
fields.desc: The Tx bit number for each channel minus 1in TDM mode.

fields.name: TX_MSB_SHIFT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable transmitter in Phillips standard mode

fields.name: TX_BCK_NO_DLY
fields.desc: 1: BCK is not delayed to generate pos/neg edge in master mode. 0: BCK is delayed to generate pos/neg edge in master mode.

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Integral I2S clock divider value

fields.name: RX_CLK_ACTIVE
fields.desc: I2S Rx module clock enable signal.

fields.name: RX_CLK_SEL
fields.desc: Select I2S Rx module source clock. 0: no clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

fields.name: MCLK_SEL
fields.desc: 0: UseI2S Tx module clock as I2S_MCLK_OUT.  1: UseI2S Rx module clock as I2S_MCLK_OUT.

fields.name: TX_CLKM_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Integral I2S TX clock divider value. f_I2S_CLK = f_I2S_CLK_S/(N+b/a). There will be (a-b) * n-div and b * (n+1)-div.  So the average combination will be:  for b <= a/2, z * [x * n-div + (n+1)-div] + y * n-div. For b > a/2, z * [n-div + x * (n+1)-div] + y * (n+1)-div.

fields.name: TX_CLK_ACTIVE
fields.desc: I2S Tx module clock enable signal.

fields.name: TX_CLK_SEL
fields.desc: Select I2S Tx module source clock. 0: XTAL clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable clk gate

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_Z
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Z is b. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Z is (a-b).

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_Y
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%b) . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%(a-b)).

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_X
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/b) - 1. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/(a-b)) - 1.

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 0 . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 1.

fields.name: TX_CLKM_DIV_Y
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%b) . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%(a-b)).

fields.name: TX_CLKM_DIV_X
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/b) - 1. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/(a-b)) - 1.

fields.name: TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1

1611202564.name: GPIO%s
1611202564.desc: IO MUX Configure Register for pad XTAL_32K_P

fields.name: MCU_OE
fields.desc: Output enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: output enabled. 0: output disabled.

fields.name: SLP_SEL
fields.desc: Sleep mode selection of this pad. Set to 1 to put the pad in pad mode.

fields.name: MCU_WPD
fields.desc: Pull-down enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: internal pull-down enabled. 0: internal pull-down disabled.

fields.name: MCU_WPU
fields.desc: Pull-up enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: internal pull-up enabled. 0: internal pull-up disabled.

fields.name: MCU_IE
fields.desc: Input enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: input enabled. 0: input disabled.

fields.name: MCU_DRV
fields.desc: Select the drive strength of the pad during sleep mode. 0: ~5 mA. 1: ~10mA. 2: ~20mA. 3: ~40mA.

fields.name: FUN_WPD
fields.desc: Pull-down enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-down enabled. 0: internal pull-down disabled.

fields.name: FUN_WPU
fields.desc: Pull-up enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-up enabled. 0: internal pull-up disabled.

fields.name: FUN_IE
fields.desc: Input enable of the pad. 1: input enabled. 0: input disabled.

fields.name: FUN_DRV
fields.desc: Select the drive strength of the pad. 0: ~5 mA. 1: ~10mA. 2: ~20mA. 3: ~40mA.

fields.name: MCU_SEL
fields.desc: Select IO MUX function for this signal. 0: Select Function 1. 1: Select Function 2. etc.

fields.name: FILTER_EN
fields.desc: Enable filter for pin input signals. 1: Filter enabled. 0: Filter disabled.

1611202748.name: MODEM_DIAG_EN
1611202748.desc: GPIO MATRIX Configure Register for modem diag

fields.name: MODEM_DIAG_EN
fields.desc: bit i to enable modem_diag[i] into gpio matrix. 1:enable modem_diag[i] into gpio matrix. 0:enable other signals into gpio matrix

fields.name: REG_DATE
fields.desc: Version control register

fields.name: TIMER_SEL
fields.desc:
This field is used to select one of timers for channel %s.

0: select timer0, 1: select timer1, 2: select timer2, 3: select timer3

fields.name: SIG_OUT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable signal output on channel %s.

fields.name: IDLE_LV
fields.desc: This bit is used to control the output value when channel %s is inactive (when LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s is 0).

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: This bit is used to update LEDC_HPOINT_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_START_CH%s, LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s, LEDC_TIMER_SEL_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_NUM_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_SCALE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_INC_CH%s, and LEDC_OVF_CNT_EN_CH%s fields for channel %s, and will be automatically cleared by hardware.

fields.name: OVF_NUM
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the maximum times of overflow minus 1.

The LEDC_OVF_CNT_CH%s_INT interrupt will be triggered when channel %s overflows for (LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH%s + 1) times.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_EN
fields.desc: This bit is used to enable the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: HPOINT
fields.desc: The output value changes to high when the selected timers has reached the value specified by this register.

fields.name: DUTY
fields.desc:
This register is used to change the output duty by controlling the Lpoint.

The output value turns to low when the selected timers has reached the Lpoint.

fields.name: DUTY_START
fields.desc: Other configured fields in LEDC_CH%s_CONF1_REG will start to take effect when this bit is set to 1.

fields.name: DUTY_CH_R
fields.desc: This register stores the current duty of output signal on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_RES
fields.desc: This register is used to control the range of the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: CLK_DIV
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the divisor for the divider in timer %s.

The least significant eight bits represent the fractional part.

fields.name: PAUSE
fields.desc: This bit is used to suspend the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: RST
fields.desc: This bit is used to reset timer %s. The counter will show 0 after reset.

fields.name: TICK_SEL
fields.desc:
This bit is used to select clock for timer %s. When this bit is set to 1 LEDC_APB_CLK_SEL[1:0] should be 1, otherwise the timer clock may be not accurate.

1'h0: SLOW_CLK 1'h1: REF_TICK

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: Set this bit to update LEDC_CLK_DIV_TIMER%s and LEDC_TIMER%s_DUTY_RES.

fields.name: TIMER_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the current counter value of timer %s.

fields.name: TIMER0_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer0 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: TIMER1_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer1 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: TIMER2_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer2 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: TIMER3_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer3 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 0. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH1_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 1. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH2_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 2. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH3_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 3. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH4_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 4. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH5_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 5. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 0. Triggered when the ovf_cnt has reached the value specified by LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH0.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH1_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 1. Triggered when the ovf_cnt has reached the value specified by LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH1.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH2_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 2. Triggered when the ovf_cnt has reached the value specified by LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH2.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH3_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 3. Triggered when the ovf_cnt has reached the value specified by LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH3.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH4_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 4. Triggered when the ovf_cnt has reached the value specified by LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH4.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_CH5_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 5. Triggered when the ovf_cnt has reached the value specified by LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH5.

fields.name: TIMER0_OVF_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt status bit for the LEDC_TIMER0_OVF_INT interrupt when LEDC_TIMER0_OVF_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: TIMER1_OVF_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt status bit for the LEDC_TIMER1_OVF_INT interrupt when LEDC_TIMER1_OVF_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: TIMER2_OVF_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt status bit for the LEDC_TIMER2_OVF_INT interrupt when LEDC_TIMER2_OVF_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: TIMER3_OVF_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt status bit for the LEDC_TIMER3_OVF_INT interrupt when LEDC_TIMER3_OVF_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH0_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt status bit for the LEDC_DUTY_CHNG_END_CH0_INT interrupt when LEDC_DUTY_CHNG_END_CH0_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: DUTY_CHNG_END_CH1_INT_ST

1611339776.name: I2C_SCL_LOW_PERIOD
1611339776.desc:
Configures the low level width of the SCL
Clock

fields.name: I2C_SCL_LOW_PERIOD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SCL remains low in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

fields.name: I2C_SDA_FORCE_OUT
fields.desc: 1: direct output, 0: open drain output.

fields.name: I2C_SCL_FORCE_OUT
fields.desc: 1: direct output, 0: open drain output.

fields.name: I2C_SAMPLE_SCL_LEVEL
fields.desc:
This register is used to select the sample mode.
1: sample SDA data on the SCL low level.
0: sample SDA data on the SCL high level.

fields.name: I2C_RX_FULL_ACK_LEVEL
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the ACK value that need to sent by master when the rx_fifo_cnt has reached the threshold.

fields.name: I2C_TRANS_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start sending the data in txfifo.

fields.name: I2C_TX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
This bit is used to control the sending mode for data needing to be sent. 
1: send data from the least significant bit,
0: send data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: I2C_RX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
This bit is used to control the storage mode for received data.
1: receive data from the least significant bit,
0: receive data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: I2C_CLK_EN
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: I2C_ARBITRATION_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for arbitration_lost.

fields.name: I2C_FSM_RST
fields.desc: This register is used to reset the scl FMS.

fields.name: I2C_CONF_UPGATE
fields.desc: synchronization bit

fields.name: I2C_RESP_REC
fields.desc: The received ACK value in master mode or slave mode. 0: ACK, 1: NACK.

fields.name: I2C_ARB_LOST
fields.desc: When the I2C controller loses control of SCL line, this register changes to 1.

fields.name: I2C_BUS_BUSY
fields.desc: 1: the I2C bus is busy transferring data, 0: the I2C bus is in idle state.

fields.name: I2C_RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: This field represents the amount of data needed to be sent.

fields.name: I2C_TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: This field stores the amount of received data in RAM.

fields.name: I2C_SCL_MAIN_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
This field indicates the states of the I2C module state machine. 
0: Idle, 1: Address shift, 2: ACK address, 3: Rx data, 4: Tx data, 5: Send ACK, 6: Wait ACK

fields.name: I2C_SCL_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
This field indicates the states of the state machine used to produce SCL.
0: Idle, 1: Start, 2: Negative edge, 3: Low, 4: Positive edge, 5: High, 6: Stop

1611339788.name: I2C_TO
1611339788.desc: Setting time out control for receiving data.

fields.name: I2C_TIME_OUT_VALUE
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the timeout for receiving a data bit in APB
clock cycles.

fields.name: I2C_TIME_OUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for time out control.

fields.name: I2C_RXFIFO_RADDR
fields.desc: This is the offset address of the APB reading from rxfifo

fields.name: I2C_RXFIFO_WADDR
fields.desc: This is the offset address of i2c module receiving data and writing to rxfifo.

fields.name: I2C_TXFIFO_RADDR
fields.desc: This is the offset address of i2c module reading from txfifo.

fields.name: I2C_TXFIFO_WADDR
fields.desc: This is the offset address of APB bus writing to txfifo.

fields.name: RXFIFO_WM_THRHD
fields.desc: The water mark threshold of rx FIFO in nonfifo access mode. When reg_reg_fifo_prt_en is 1 and rx FIFO counter is bigger than reg_rxfifo_wm_thrhd[3:0], reg_rxfifo_wm_int_raw bit will be valid.

fields.name: TXFIFO_WM_THRHD
fields.desc: The water mark threshold of tx FIFO in nonfifo access mode. When reg_reg_fifo_prt_en is 1 and tx FIFO counter is smaller than reg_txfifo_wm_thrhd[3:0], reg_txfifo_wm_int_raw bit will be valid.

fields.name: NONFIFO_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable APB nonfifo access.

fields.name: RX_FIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset rx-fifo.

fields.name: TX_FIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset tx-fifo.

fields.name: FIFO_PRT_EN
fields.desc: The control enable bit of FIFO pointer in non-fifo access mode. This bit controls the valid bits and the interrupts of tx/rx_fifo overflow, underflow, full and empty.

fields.name: I2C_FIFO_RDATA
fields.desc: The value of rx FIFO read data.

1611339824.name: I2C_SDA_HOLD
1611339824.desc: Configures the hold time after a negative SCL edge.

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time to hold the data after the negative
edge of SCL, in I2C module clock cycles.

1611339828.name: I2C_SDA_SAMPLE
1611339828.desc: Configures the sample time after a positive SCL edge.

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SDA is sampled, in I2C module clock cycles.

1611339832.name: I2C_SCL_HIGH_PERIOD
1611339832.desc: Configures the high level width of SCL

fields.name: I2C_SCL_HIGH_PERIOD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SCL setup to high level and remains high in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

fields.name: I2C_SCL_WAIT_HIGH_PERIOD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for the SCL_FSM's waiting period for SCL high level in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

1611339840.name: I2C_SCL_START_HOLD
1611339840.desc: Configures the delay between the SDA and SCL negative edge for a start condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time between the negative edge
of SDA and the negative edge of SCL for a START condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

1611339844.name: I2C_SCL_RSTART_SETUP
1611339844.desc:
Configures the delay between the positive
edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time between the positive
edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA for a RESTART condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

1611339848.name: I2C_SCL_STOP_HOLD
1611339848.desc:
Configures the delay after the SCL clock
edge for a stop condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the delay after the STOP condition,
in I2C module clock cycles.

1611339852.name: I2C_SCL_STOP_SETUP
1611339852.desc:
Configures the delay between the SDA and
SCL positive edge for a stop condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the time between the positive edge
of SCL and the positive edge of SDA, in I2C module clock cycles.

1611339856.name: I2C_FILTER_CFG
1611339856.desc: SCL and SDA filter configuration register

fields.name: I2C_SCL_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc:
When a pulse on the SCL input has smaller width than this register value
in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

fields.name: I2C_SDA_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc:
When a pulse on the SDA input has smaller width than this register value
in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

fields.name: I2C_SCL_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the filter enable bit for SCL.

fields.name: I2C_SDA_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the filter enable bit for SDA.

fields.name: I2C_SCLK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: the integral part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

fields.name: I2C_SCLK_DIV_A
fields.desc: the numerator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

fields.name: I2C_SCLK_DIV_B
fields.desc: the denominator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

fields.name: I2C_SCLK_SEL
fields.desc: The clock selection for i2c module:0-XTAL,1-CLK_8MHz.

fields.name: I2C_SCLK_ACTIVE
fields.desc: The clock switch for i2c module

fields.name: I2C_COMMAND0
fields.desc:
This is the content of command 0. It consists of three parts: 
op_code is the command, 0: RSTART, 1: WRITE, 2: READ, 3: STOP, 4: END.
Byte_num represents the number of bytes that need to be sent or received.
ack_check_en, ack_exp and ack are used to control the ACK bit. See I2C cmd structure for more
Information.

fields.name: I2C_COMMAND0_DONE
fields.desc:
When command 0 is done in I2C Master mode, this bit changes to high
level.

fields.name: I2C_SCL_PD_EN
fields.desc: The power down enable bit for the I2C output SCL line. 1: Power down. 0: Not power down. Set reg_scl_force_out and reg_scl_pd_en to 1 to stretch SCL low.

fields.name: I2C_SDA_PD_EN

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than what rxfifo_full_thrhd specifies.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the amount of data in Tx-FIFO is less than what txfifo_empty_thrhd specifies .

fields.name: PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a parity error in the data.

fields.name: FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a data frame error .

fields.name: RXFIFO_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than the FIFO can store.

fields.name: DSR_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of DSRn signal.

fields.name: CTS_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of CTSn signal.

fields.name: BRK_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a 0 after the stop bit.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TOUT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver takes more time than rx_tout_thrhd to receive a byte.

fields.name: SW_XON_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver recevies Xon char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: SW_XOFF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives Xoff char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: GLITCH_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a glitch in the middle of a start bit.

fields.name: TX_BRK_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter completes  sending  NULL characters after all data in Tx-FIFO are sent.

fields.name: TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has kept the shortest duration after sending the  last data.

fields.name: TX_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has send out all data in FIFO.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the configured at_cmd char.

fields.name: WAKEUP_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when input rxd edge changes more times than what reg_active_threshold specifies in light sleeping mode.

fields.name: STOP_BIT_NUM

fields.name: DIS_RX_DAT_OVF
fields.desc: Disable UART Rx data overflow detect.

fields.name: ERR_WR_MASK
fields.desc: 1'h1: Receiver stops storing data into FIFO when data is wrong. 1'h0: Receiver stores the data even if the  received data is wrong.

fields.name: MEM_CLK_EN
fields.desc: UART memory clock gate enable signal.

fields.name: SW_RTS
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software rts signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart receive-FIFO.

fields.name: TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart transmit-FIFO.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce rxfifo_full_int interrupt when receiver receives more data than this register value.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce txfifo_empty_int interrupt when the data amount in Tx-FIFO is less than this register value.

fields.name: CTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart cts signal.

fields.name: DSR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dsr signal.

fields.name: RTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rts signal.

fields.name: DTR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dtr signal.

fields.name: SW_DTR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software dtr signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum amount of data that can be received  when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: This is the flow enable bit for UART receiver.

fields.name: WK_CHAR1
fields.desc: This register restores the specified wake up char1 to wake up

fields.name: WK_CHAR2

fields.name: WK_CHAR0
fields.desc: This register restores the specified char0 to wake up

fields.name: ACTIVE_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: The uart is activated from light sleeping mode when the input rxd edge changes more times than this register value.

fields.name: RX_WAKE_UP_THRHD
fields.desc: In wake up mode 1 this field is used to set the received data number threshold to wake up chip.

fields.name: WK_CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to select number of wake up char.

fields.name: WK_CHAR_MASK
fields.desc: This register is used to mask  wake up char.

fields.name: WK_MODE_SEL
fields.desc: This register is used to select wake up mode. 0: RXD toggling to wake up. 1: received data number larger than

fields.name: XON_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xon flow control char.

fields.name: XOFF_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xoff flow control char.

fields.name: XON_XOFF_STILL_SEND
fields.desc: In software flow control mode, UART Tx is disabled once UART Rx receives XOFF. In this status, UART Tx can not transmit XOFF even the received data number is larger than UART_XOFF_THRESHOLD. Set this bit to enable UART Tx can transmit XON/XOFF when UART Tx is disabled.

fields.name: SW_FLOW_CON_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable software flow control. It is used with register sw_xon or sw_xoff.

fields.name: XONOFF_DEL
fields.desc: Set this bit to remove flow control char from the received data.

fields.name: FORCE_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the transmitter to go on sending data.

fields.name: FORCE_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the  transmitter from sending data.

fields.name: SEND_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xon char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: SEND_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xoff char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: XON_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is less than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1  it will send a Xon char.

fields.name: XOFF_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is more than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1  it will send a Xoff char.

fields.name: TX_BRK_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the number of 0 to be sent after the process of sending data is done. It is active when txd_brk is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_IDLE_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce frame end signal when receiver takes more time to receive one byte data than this register value.

fields.name: TX_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers.

fields.name: DL0_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: DL1_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: PRE_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first at_cmd is received by receiver.

fields.name: POST_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the last at_cmd and the next data.

fields.name: RX_GAP_TOUT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the at_cmd chars.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the content of at_cmd char.

fields.name: CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the num of continuous at_cmd chars received by receiver.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power down UART memory.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power up UART memory.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the enble bit for uart receiver's timeout function.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_FLOW_DIS
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop accumulating idle_cnt when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the threshold time that receiver takes to receive one byte. The rxfifo_tout_int interrupt will be trigger when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte with rx_tout_en set to 1.

1610694660.name: TIMER0_CFG0
1610694660.desc: PWM timer0 period and update method configuration register.

fields.name: TIMER0_PRESCALE
fields.desc: period of PT0_clk = Period of PWM_clk * (PWM_TIMER0_PRESCALE + 1)

fields.name: TIMER0_PERIOD
fields.desc: period shadow register of PWM timer0

fields.name: TIMER0_PERIOD_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Update method for active register of PWM timer0 period, 0: immediate, 1: TEZ, 2: sync, 3: TEZ | sync. TEZ here and below means timer equal zero event

1610694664.name: TIMER0_CFG1
1610694664.desc: PWM timer0 working mode and start/stop control configuration register.

fields.name: TIMER0_START
fields.desc: PWM timer0 start and stop control. 0: if PWM timer0 starts, then stops at TEZ, 1: if timer0 starts, then stops at TEP, 2: PWM timer0 starts and runs on, 3: timer0 starts and stops at the next TEZ, 4: timer0 starts and stops at the next TEP. TEP here and below means the event that happens when the timer equals to period

fields.name: TIMER0_MOD
fields.desc: PWM timer0 working mode, 0: freeze, 1: increase mode, 2: decrease mode, 3: up-down mode

1610694668.name: TIMER0_SYNC

fields.name: TIMER0_SYNCI_EN

fields.name: SW
fields.desc: Toggling this bit will trigger a software sync.

fields.name: TIMER0_SYNCO_SEL
fields.desc: PWM timer0 sync_out selection, 0: sync_in, 1: TEZ, 2: TEP, and sync out will always generate when toggling the reg_timer0_sync_sw bit

fields.name: TIMER0_PHASE
fields.desc: phase for timer reload on sync event

fields.name: TIMER0_PHASE_DIRECTION
fields.desc: Configure the PWM timer0's direction when timer0 mode is up-down mode: 0-increase,1-decrease

fields.name: TIMER0_VALUE

fields.name: EN
fields.desc: Force clock on for this register file

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: Version of this register file

fields.name: LOG_ENA
fields.desc: enable bus log. BIT0: hp-cpu, BIT1: lp-cpu, BIT2: DMA.

fields.name: LOG_MODE
fields.desc: This field must be onehot. 4'b0001 : WR monitor, 4'b0010: WORD monitor, 4'b0100: HALFWORD monitor, 4'b1000: BYTE monitor.

fields.name: LOG_MEM_LOOP_ENABLE
fields.desc: Set 1 enable mem_loop, it will loop write at the range of MEM_START and MEM_END

fields.name: LOG_CHECK_DATA
fields.desc: The special check data, when write this special data, it will trigger logging.

fields.name: LOG_DATA_MASK
fields.desc: byte mask enable, BIT0 mask the first byte of MEM_MONITOR_LOG_CHECK_DATA, and BIT1 mask second byte, and so on.

fields.name: LOG_MIN
fields.desc: the min address of log range

fields.name: LOG_MAX
fields.desc: the max address of log range

fields.name: LOG_MEM_START
fields.desc: the start address of writing logging message

fields.name: LOG_MEM_END
fields.desc: the end address of writing logging message

fields.name: LOG_MEM_CURRENT_ADDR
fields.desc: means next writing address

fields.name: LOG_MEM_ADDR_UPDATE
fields.desc: Set 1 to updata MEM_MONITOR_LOG_MEM_CURRENT_ADDR, when set 1, MEM_MONITOR_LOG_MEM_CURRENT_ADDR will update to MEM_MONITOR_LOG_MEM_START

fields.name: LOG_MEM_FULL_FLAG
fields.desc: 1 means memory write loop at least one time at the range of MEM_START and MEM_END

fields.name: CLR_LOG_MEM_FULL_FLAG
fields.desc: Set 1 to clr MEM_MONITOR_LOG_MEM_FULL_FLAG

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Set 1 to force on the clk of mem_monitor register

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: version register

fields.name: RX_PULSE_SUBMODE_SEL
fields.desc:
Pulse submode selection. 
0000: positive pulse start(data bit included) &&  positive pulse end(data bit included)
0001: positive pulse start(data bit included) && positive pulse end (data bit excluded)
0010: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && positive pulse end (data bit included)
0011: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && positive pulse end (data bit excluded)
0100: positive pulse start(data bit included) && length end
0101: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && length end
0110: negative pulse start(data bit included) &&  negative pulse end(data bit included)
0111: negative pulse start(data bit included) && negative pulse end (data bit excluded)
1000: negative pulse start(data bit excluded) && negative pulse end (data bit included)
1001: negative pulse start(data bit excluded) && negative pulse end (data bit excluded)
1010: negative pulse start(data bit included) && length end
1011: negative pulse start(data bit excluded) && length end

fields.name: RX_SMP_MODE_SEL
fields.desc:
Rx data sampling mode selection. 
000: external level enable mode
001: external pulse enable mode  
010: internal software enable mode

fields.name: RX_CLK_EDGE_SEL
fields.desc: Write 0 to enable sampling data on the rising edge of rx clock. Write 0 to enable sampling data on the falling edge of rx clock.

fields.name: RX_BIT_PACK_ORDER
fields.desc: Write 0 to pack bits into 1byte from MSB when data bus width is 4/2/1 bits. Write 0 to pack bits into 1byte from LSB when data bus width is 4/2/1 bits.

fields.name: RX_BUS_WID_SEL
fields.desc:
Rx data bus width selection. 
100: bus width is 1 bit 
011: bus width is 2 bits 
010: bus width is 4 bits
001: bus width is 8 bits
000: bus width is 16 bits

fields.name: CH0_NEG_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a negative edge.

1: Increase the counter.2: Decrease the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH0_POS_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a positive edge.

1: Increase the counter.2: Decrease the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH0_HCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH0_LCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH1_NEG_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a negative edge.

1: Increment the counter.2: Decrement the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH1_POS_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a positive edge.

1: Increment the counter.2: Decrement the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH1_HCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH1_LCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Integral I2S TX clock divider value. f_I2S_CLK = f_I2S_CLK_S/(N+b/a). There will be (a-b) * n-div and b * (n+1)-div.  So the average combination will be:  for b <= a/2, z * [x * n-div + (n+1)-div] + y * n-div. For b > a/2, z * [n-div + x * (n+1)-div] + y * (n+1)-div.

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_SEL
fields.desc: Select I2S Tx module source clock. 0: XTAL clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_EN
fields.desc: Set 1 to enable i2s_tx function clock

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Z
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Z is b. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Z is (a-b).

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%b) . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%(a-b)).

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/b) - 1. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/(a-b)) - 1.

fields.name: I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 0 . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 1.

fields.name: I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Integral I2S clock divider value

fields.name: I2S_RX_CLKM_SEL
fields.desc: Select I2S Rx module source clock. 0: no clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

fields.name: I2S_RX_CLKM_EN
fields.desc: Set 1 to enable i2s_rx function clock

fields.name: I2S_MCLK_SEL
fields.desc: This field is used to select master-clock. 0(default): clk_i2s_rx, 1: clk_i2s_tx

fields.name: I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Z
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Z is b. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Z is (a-b).

fields.name: I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%b) . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%(a-b)).

fields.name: I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/b) - 1. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/(a-b)) - 1.

fields.name: I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 0 . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 1.

fields.desc: clk_hproot is div1 of low-speed clock-source if clck-source is a low-speed clock-source such as XTAL/FOSC.

fields.desc: clk_hproot is div3 of SPLL if the clock-source is high-speed clock SPLL.

fields.name: PLL_FREQ_SEL

fields.name: CPU_WAITI_DELAY_NUM
fields.desc: This field used to set delay cycle when cpu enter waiti mode, after delay waiti_clk will close

fields.name: CPU_LS_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Set as one within (0,1,3) to generate clk_cpu drived by clk_hproot. The clk_cpu is div1(default)/div2/div4 of clk_hproot. This field is only avaliable for low-speed clock-source such as XTAL/FOSC, and should be used together with PCR_AHB_LS_DIV_NUM.

fields.name: CPU_HS_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Set as one within (0,1,3) to generate clk_cpu drived by clk_hproot. The clk_cpu is div1(default)/div2/div4 of clk_hproot. This field is only avaliable for high-speed clock-source such as SPLL, and should be used together with PCR_AHB_HS_DIV_NUM.

fields.name: CPU_HS_120M_FORCE
fields.desc: Given that PCR_CPU_HS_DIV_NUM is 0, set this field as 1 to force clk_cpu at 120MHz. Only avaliable when PCR_CPU_HS_DIV_NUM is 0 and clk_cpu is driven by SPLL.

fields.name: AHB_LS_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Set as one within (0,1,3,7) to generate clk_ahb drived by clk_hproot. The clk_ahb is div1(default)/div2/div4/div8 of clk_hproot. This field is only avaliable for low-speed clock-source such as XTAL/FOSC, and should be used together with PCR_CPU_LS_DIV_NUM.

fields.name: AHB_HS_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Set as one within (3,7,15) to generate clk_ahb drived by clk_hproot. The clk_ahb is div4(default)/div8/div16 of clk_hproot. This field is only avaliable for high-speed clock-source such as SPLL, and should be used together with PCR_CPU_HS_DIV_NUM.

fields.name: APB_DECREASE_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: If this field's value is grater than PCR_APB_DIV_NUM, the clk_apb will be automatically down to clk_apb_decrease only when no access is on apb-bus, and will recover to the previous frequency when a new access appears on apb-bus. Set as one within (0,1,3) to set clk_apb_decrease as div1/div2/div4(default) of clk_ahb. Note that enable this function will reduce performance. Users can set this field as zero to disable the auto-decrease-apb-freq function. By default, this function is disable.

fields.name: APB_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Set as one within (0,1,3) to generate clk_apb drived by clk_ahb. The clk_apb is div1(default)/div2/div4 of clk_ahb.
