1610637312.name: CH%sDATA
1610637312.desc: The read and write  data register for CHANNEL%s by apb fifo access.

fields.name: DATA
fields.desc: Read and write data for channel %s via APB FIFO.

fields.name: TX_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start sending data on CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_RD_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset read ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing transmitter.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

fields.name: TX_CONTI_MODE
fields.desc: Set this bit to restart transmission  from the first data to the last data in CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_TX_WRAP_EN
fields.desc: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume sending at the start when the data to be sent is more than its memory size.

fields.name: IDLE_OUT_LV
fields.desc: This bit configures the level of output signal in CHANNEL%s when the latter is in IDLE state.

fields.name: IDLE_OUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the output enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s in IDLE state.

fields.name: TX_STOP
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the transmitter of CHANNEL%s sending data out.

fields.name: DIV_CNT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: CARRIER_EFF_EN
fields.desc: 1: Add carrier modulation on the output signal only at the send data state for CHANNEL%s. 0: Add carrier modulation on the output signal at all state for CHANNEL%s. Only valid when RMT_CARRIER_EN_CH%s is 1.

fields.name: CARRIER_EN
fields.desc: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

fields.name: CARRIER_OUT_LV
fields.desc:
This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.

1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.

1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

fields.name: AFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: CONF_UPDATE
fields.desc: synchronization bit for CHANNEL%s

fields.name: DIV_CNT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: IDLE_THRES
fields.desc: When no edge is detected on the input signal and continuous clock cycles is longer than this register value, received process is finished.

fields.name: MEM_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: CARRIER_EN
fields.desc: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

fields.name: CARRIER_OUT_LV
fields.desc:
This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.

1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.

1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

fields.name: RX_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver to receive data on CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_WR_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset write ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing receiver.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

fields.name: MEM_OWNER
fields.desc:
This register marks the ownership of CHANNEL%s's ram block.

1'h1: Receiver is using the ram. 

1'h0: APB bus is using the ram.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the receive filter's enable bit for CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc: Ignores the input pulse when its width is smaller than this register value in APB clock periods (in receive mode).

fields.name: MEM_RX_WRAP_EN
fields.desc: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume receiving at the start when the data to be received is more than its memory size.

fields.name: AFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: CONF_UPDATE
fields.desc: synchronization bit for CHANNEL%s

fields.name: MEM_RADDR_EX
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when transmitter of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: This register records the FSM status of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: APB_MEM_WADDR
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when writes RAM over APB bus.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RD_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when reading via APB bus.

fields.name: MEM_EMPTY
fields.desc: This status bit will be set when the data to be set is more than memory size and the wraparound mode is disabled.

fields.name: APB_MEM_WR_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when writes via APB bus.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RADDR
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when reading RAM over APB bus.

fields.name: MEM_WADDR_EX
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when receiver of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RADDR
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when reads RAM over APB bus.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: This register records the FSM status of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_OWNER_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set when the ownership of memory block is wrong.

fields.name: MEM_FULL
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the receiver receives more data than the memory size.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RD_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when reads via APB bus.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_END
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL%s. Triggered when transmission done.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_END
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL2. Triggered when reception done.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_ERR
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL4. Triggered when error occurs.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_ERR
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL6. Triggered when error occurs.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_THR_EVENT
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL%s. Triggered when transmitter sent more data than configured value.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_THR_EVENT
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL2. Triggered when receiver receive more data than configured value.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_LOOP
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL%s. Triggered when the loop count reaches the configured threshold value.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_END
fields.desc: The masked interrupt status bit for CH%s_TX_END_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_END
fields.desc: The masked interrupt status bit for CH2_RX_END_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_ERR
fields.desc: The masked interrupt status bit for CH4_ERR_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_ERR
fields.desc: The masked interrupt status bit for CH6_ERR_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_THR_EVENT
fields.desc: The masked interrupt status bit for CH%s_TX_THR_EVENT_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_THR_EVENT
fields.desc: The masked interrupt status bit for CH2_RX_THR_EVENT_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_X_LOOP
fields.desc: The masked interrupt status bit for CH%s_TX_LOOP_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_END
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for CH%s_TX_END_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_END
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for CH2_RX_END_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_ERR
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for CH4_ERR_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_ERR
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for CH6_ERR_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_THR_EVENT
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for CH%s_TX_THR_EVENT_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_THR_EVENT
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for CH2_RX_THR_EVENT_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_X_LOOP
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for CH%s_TX_LOOP_INT.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_END
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear theCH%s_TX_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_END
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear theCH2_RX_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_ERR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear theCH4_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_ERR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear theCH6_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_THR_EVENT
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear theCH%s_TX_THR_EVENT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_THR_EVENT
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear theCH2_RX_THR_EVENT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_LOOP
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear theCH%s_TX_LOOP_INT interrupt.

fields.name: CARRIER_LOW
fields.desc: This register is used to configure carrier wave 's low level clock period for CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: CARRIER_HIGH
fields.desc: This register is used to configure carrier wave 's high level clock period for CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: CARRIER_LOW_THRES
fields.desc: The low level period in a carrier modulation mode is (REG_RMT_REG_CARRIER_LOW_THRES_CH%s + 1) for channel %s.

fields.name: CARRIER_HIGH_THRES
fields.desc: The high level period in a carrier modulation mode is (REG_RMT_REG_CARRIER_HIGH_THRES_CH%s + 1) for channel %s.

fields.name: TX_LIM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum entries that CHANNEL%s can send out.

fields.name: TX_LOOP_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum loop count when tx_conti_mode is valid.

fields.name: TX_LOOP_CNT_EN
fields.desc: This register is the enabled bit for loop count.

fields.name: LOOP_COUNT_RESET
fields.desc: This register is used to reset the loop count when tx_conti_mode is valid.

fields.name: LOOP_STOP_EN
fields.desc: This bit is used to enable the loop send stop function after the loop counter counts to  loop number for CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: RMT_RX_LIM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum entries that CHANNEL%s can receive.

fields.name: APB_FIFO_MASK
fields.desc: 1'h1: access memory directly.   1'h0: access memory by FIFO.

fields.name: MEM_CLK_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the clock for RMT memory.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to power down RMT memory.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: 1: Disable RMT memory light sleep power down function. 0: Power down RMT memory when RMT is in light sleep mode.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: the integral part of the fractional divisor

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_A
fields.desc: the numerator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_B
fields.desc: the denominator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor

fields.name: SCLK_SEL
fields.desc: choose the clock source of rmt_sclk. 1:CLK_80Mhz,2:CLK_FOSC, 3:XTAL

fields.name: SCLK_ACTIVE
fields.desc: rmt_sclk switch

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: RMT register clock gate enable signal. 1: Power up the drive clock of registers. 0: Power down the drive clock of registers

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: clock enable

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: date

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST
fields.desc: The current status of SPI0 master FSM: spi0_mst_st. 0: idle state, 1:SPI0_GRANT , 2: program/erase suspend state, 3: SPI0 read data state, 4: wait cache/EDMA sent data is stored in SPI0 TX FIFO, 5: SPI0 write data state.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST
fields.desc: The current status of SPI0 slave FSM: mspi_st. 0: idle state, 1: preparation state, 2: send command state, 3: send address state, 4: wait state, 5: read data state, 6:write data state, 7: done state, 8: read data end state.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR
fields.desc: SPI0 USR_CMD start bit, only used when SPI_MEM_AXI_REQ_EN is cleared.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WDUMMY_DQS_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_DQS is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WDUMMY_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_RIN
fields.desc: In an MSPI read data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller in the first half part of dummy phase. It is used to mask invalid SPI_DQS in the half part of dummy phase.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_WOUT
fields.desc: In an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller in the second half part of dummy phase. It is used to pre-drive flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during write-data phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during read-data phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during address phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FASTRD_MODE
fields.desc: This bit enable the bits: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_QOUT and SPI_MEM_FREAD_DOUT. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: SPI_MEM_D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WP
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DQS_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to flash, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_DQS are always 1. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DATA_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to flash, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_IO[7:0] are always 1. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is alwasy on.

fields.name: SPI_AR_SIZE0_1_SUPPORT_EN
fields.desc: 1: MSPI supports ARSIZE 0~3. When ARSIZE =0~2, MSPI read address is 4*n and reply the real AXI read data back. 0: When ARSIZE 0~1, MSPI reply SLV_ERR.

fields.name: SPI_AW_SIZE0_1_SUPPORT_EN
fields.desc: 1: MSPI supports AWSIZE 0~3. 0: When AWSIZE 0~1, MSPI reply SLV_ERR.

fields.name: SPI_AXI_RDATA_BACK_FAST
fields.desc: 1: Reply AXI read data to AXI bus when one AXI read beat data is available. 0: Reply AXI read data to AXI bus when all the read data is available.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RRESP_ECC_ERR_EN
fields.desc: 1: RRESP is SLV_ERR when there is a ECC error in AXI read data. 0: RRESP is OKAY when there is a ECC error in AXI read data. The ECC error information is recorded in SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR_REG.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AR_SPLICE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable AXI Read Splice-transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AW_SPLICE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable AXI Write Splice-transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RAM0_EN
fields.desc: When SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN is 0 and SPI_MEM_RAM0_EN is 1, only EXT_RAM0 will be accessed. When SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN is 0 and SPI_MEM_RAM0_EN is 0, only EXT_RAM1 will be accessed. When SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN is 1,  EXT_RAM0 and EXT_RAM1 will be accessed at the same time.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable DUAL-RAM mode, EXT_RAM0 and EXT_RAM1 will be accessed at the same time.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FAST_WRITE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to write data faster, do not wait write data has been stored in tx_bus_fifo_l2. It will wait 4*T_clk_ctrl to insure the write data has been stored in  tx_bus_fifo_l2.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: The synchronous reset signal for SPI0 RX AFIFO and all the AES_MSPI SYNC FIFO to receive signals from AXI.  Set this bit to reset these FIFO.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: The synchronous reset signal for SPI0 TX AFIFO and all the AES_MSPI SYNC FIFO to send signals to AXI. Set this bit to reset these FIFO.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles-1) of prepare phase by SPI Bus clock, this bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI CS signal is delayed to inactive by SPI bus clock, this bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_TIME + SPI_MEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME is the SPI0 CS hold cycle in ECC mode when accessed flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_SKIP_PAGE_CORNER
fields.desc: 1: SPI0 and SPI1 skip page corner when accesses flash. 0: Not skip page corner when accesses flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_16TO18_BYTE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 and SPI1 ECC 16 bytes data with 2 ECC bytes mode when accesses flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SPLIT_TRANS_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 split one AXI read flash transfer into two SPI transfers when one transfer will cross flash or EXT_RAM page corner, valid no matter whether there is an ECC region or not.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY
fields.desc: These bits are used to set the minimum CS high time tSHSL between SPI burst transfer when accesses to flash. tSHSL is (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY[5:0] + 1) MSPI core clock cycles.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SYNC_RESET
fields.desc: The spi0_mst_st and spi0_slv_st will be reset.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_mem_clkcnt_N.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_mem_clk. So spi_mem_clk frequency is system/(spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: 1: 1-division mode, the frequency of SPI bus clock equals to that of MSPI module clock.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD
fields.desc: spi cs keep low when spi is in  done  phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP
fields.desc: spi cs is enable when spi is in  prepare  phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: The bit combined with SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE bit to control SPI clock mode 0~3.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The length in spi_mem_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DBYTELEN
fields.desc: SPI0 USR_CMD read or write data byte length -1

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of  command.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits in the flash fast read mode  it is combined with spi_mem_fastrd_mode bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FSUB_PIN
fields.desc: For SPI0,  flash is connected to SUBPINs.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SSUB_PIN
fields.desc: For SPI0,  sram is connected to SUBPINs.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: SPI_CLK line is high when idle     0: spi clk line is low when idle

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
fields.desc: SPI_CS line keep low when the bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_REQ_EN
fields.desc: For SPI0, AXI master access enable, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_USR_ADDR_4BYTE
fields.desc: For SPI0,  cache  read flash with 4 bytes address, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_FLASH_USR_CMD
fields.desc: For SPI0,  cache  read flash for user define command, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, din phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, dout phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, address phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, din phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, dout phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

fields.name: SPI_SAME_AW_AR_ADDR_CHK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to check AXI read/write the same address region.

fields.name: SPI_CLOSE_AXI_INF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to close AXI read/write transfer to MSPI, which means that only SLV_ERR will be replied to BRESP/RRESP.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_USR_SADDR_4BYTE
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, cache read flash with 4 bytes command, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_SRAM_DIO
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, spi dual I/O mode enable, 1: enable, 0:disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_SRAM_QIO
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, spi quad I/O mode enable, 1: enable, 0:disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_WR_SRAM_DUMMY
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the enable bit of dummy phase for write operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_RD_SRAM_DUMMY
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the enable bit of dummy phase for read operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_RCMD
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode cache read external RAM for user define command.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_RDUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the length in bits of read dummy phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_WCMD
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode cache write sram for user define command

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_OCT
fields.desc: reserved

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_WDUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the length in bits of write dummy phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

1610620996.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_CMD
1610620996.desc: SPI0 external RAM mode control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is always on.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SWB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits in the external RAM fast read mode  it is combined with spi_mem_fastrd_mode bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , address phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , cmd phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SADDR_OCT

fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi0_slv_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. It means that SPI_CS raises high. 0: Others

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi0_mst_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is set and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is cleared, this bit is triggered when the error times of SPI0/1 ECC read flash are equal or bigger than SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is cleared and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is set, this bit is triggered when the error times of SPI0/1 ECC read external RAM are equal or bigger than SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN are set, this bit is triggered when the total error times of SPI0/1 ECC read external RAM and flash are equal or bigger than SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN are cleared, this bit will not be triggered.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_RAW

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_INT_RAW

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FLASH_ERR_INT_RAW

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when AXI write address is invalid by compared to MMU configuration. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_EN
fields.desc: 1: in DDR mode,  0 in SDR mode

fields.desc: Set the bit to enable variable dummy cycle in spi DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_RDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder rx data of the word in spi DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_WDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder tx data of the word in spi DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_CMD_DIS
fields.desc: the bit is used to disable dual edge in command phase when DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OUTMINBYTELEN
fields.desc: It is the minimum output data length in the panda device.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_TX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in SPI0 ECC DDR write mode, when accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_RX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in SPI0 ECC DDR read mode, when accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_USR_DDR_DQS_THD
fields.desc: The delay number of data strobe which from memory based on SPI clock.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP
fields.desc: 1: Do not need the input of SPI_DQS signal, SPI0 starts to receive data when spi0_slv_st is in SPI_MEM_DIN state. It is used when there is no SPI_DQS signal or SPI_DQS signal is not stable. 0: SPI0 starts to store data at the positive and negative edge of SPI_DQS.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the differential SPI_CLK#.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DQS_CA_IN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the input of SPI_DQS signal in SPI phases of CMD and ADDR.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_DUMMY_2X
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the vary dummy function in SPI HyperBus mode, when SPI0 accesses flash or SPI1 accesses flash or sram.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert SPI_DIFF when accesses to flash. .

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OCTA_RAM_ADDR
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable octa_ram address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[25:4], 6'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1], 1'b0}.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_CA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable HyperRAM address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[19:4], 13'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1]}.

fields.desc: This bits show the first SPI1 access error address. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PM_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0/1 transfer permission control function.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_LD
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 write access error. 0: No write access error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_ST
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 read access error. 0: No read access error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_MULTI_HIT
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 access is rejected because of address miss. 0: No address miss error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_IVD
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 access is rejected because of address multi-hit. 0: No address multi-hit error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to calculate the error times of MSPI ECC read when accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_PAGE_SIZE
fields.desc: Set the page size of the flash accessed by MSPI. 0: 256 bytes. 1: 512 bytes. 2: 1024 bytes. 3: 2048 bytes.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_ECC_ADDR_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable MSPI ECC address conversion, no matter MSPI accesses to the ECC region or non-ECC region of flash. If there is no ECC region in flash, this bit should be 0. Otherwise, this bit should be 1.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ECC_ADDR_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable ECC address convert in SPI0/1 USR_CMD transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_CONTINUE_RECORD_ERR_EN
fields.desc: 1: The error information in SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_BITS and SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR is updated when there is an ECC error. 0: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_BITS and SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR record the first ECC error information.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_BITS
fields.desc: Records the first ECC error bit number in the 16 bytes(From 0~127, corresponding to byte 0 bit 0 to byte 15 bit 7)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR
fields.desc: This bits show the first MSPI ECC error address. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: This bits show the error times of MSPI ECC read. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_ERR_ADDR
fields.desc: This bits show the first AXI write/read invalid error or AXI write flash error address. It is cleared by when SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT_CLR, SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FLASH_ERR_IN_CLR or SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_IN_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ALL_FIFO_EMPTY

fields.name: SPI_RDATA_AFIFO_REMPTY
fields.desc: 1: RDATA_AFIFO is empty. 0: At least one AXI read transfer is pending.

fields.name: SPI_RADDR_AFIFO_REMPTY
fields.desc: 1: AXI_RADDR_CTL_AFIFO is empty. 0: At least one AXI read transfer is pending.

fields.name: SPI_WDATA_AFIFO_REMPTY
fields.desc: 1: WDATA_AFIFO is empty. 0: At least one AXI write transfer is pending.

fields.name: SPI_WBLEN_AFIFO_REMPTY
fields.desc: 1: WBLEN_AFIFO is empty. 0: At least one AXI write transfer is pending.

fields.name: SPI_ALL_AXI_TRANS_AFIFO_EMPTY
fields.desc: This bit is set when WADDR_AFIFO, WBLEN_AFIFO, WDATA_AFIFO, AXI_RADDR_CTL_AFIFO and RDATA_AFIFO are empty and spi0_mst_st is IDLE.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to calculate the error times of MSPI ECC read when accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_PAGE_SIZE
fields.desc: Set the page size of the external RAM accessed by MSPI. 0: 256 bytes. 1: 512 bytes. 2: 1024 bytes. 3: 2048 bytes.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_ADDR_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable MSPI ECC address conversion, no matter MSPI accesses to the ECC region or non-ECC region of external RAM. If there is no ECC region in external RAM, this bit should be 0. Otherwise, this bit should be 1.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_TIMING_CLK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable timing adjust clock for all reading operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_TIMING_CALI
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable timing auto-calibration for all reading operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: add extra dummy spi clock cycle length for spi clock calibration.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DLL_TIMING_CALI
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable DLL for timing calibration in DDR mode when accessed to flash.

fields.name: UPDATE
fields.desc: Set this bit to update delay mode, delay num and extra dummy in MSPI.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DLL_TIMING_CALI

1610621344.name: SPI_SMEM_AC
1610621344.desc: MSPI external RAM ECC and SPI CS timing control register

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_SETUP
fields.desc: For SPI0 and SPI1, spi cs is enable when spi is in prepare phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD
fields.desc: For SPI0 and SPI1, spi cs keep low when spi is in done phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: For spi0, (cycles-1) of prepare phase by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_mem_cs_setup bit.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: For SPI0 and SPI1, spi cs signal is delayed to inactive by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_mem_cs_hold bit.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD_TIME + SPI_SMEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME is the SPI0 and SPI1 CS hold cycles in ECC mode when accessed external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_SKIP_PAGE_CORNER
fields.desc: 1: SPI0 skips page corner when accesses external RAM. 0: Not skip page corner when accesses external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_16TO18_BYTE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 and SPI1 ECC 16 bytes data with 2 ECC bytes mode when accesses external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY
fields.desc: These bits are used to set the minimum CS high time tSHSL between SPI burst transfer when accesses to external RAM. tSHSL is (SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY[5:0] + 1) MSPI core clock cycles.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_SPLIT_TRANS_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 split one AXI accesses EXT_RAM transfer into two SPI transfers when one transfer will cross flash/EXT_RAM page corner, valid no matter whether there is an ECC region or not.

fields.name: SPI_CLK_EN
fields.desc: Register clock gate enable signal. 1: Enable. 0: Disable.

1610621696.name: SPI_MEM_XTS_PLAIN_BASE
1610621696.desc: The base address of the memory that stores plaintext in Manual Encryption

fields.name: SPI_XTS_PLAIN
fields.desc: This field is only used to generate include file in c case. This field is useless. Please do not use this field.

fields.name: SPI_XTS_LINESIZE
fields.desc: This bits stores the line-size parameter which will be used in manual encryption calculation. It decides how many bytes will be encrypted one time. 0: 16-bytes, 1: 32-bytes, 2: 64-bytes, 3:reserved.

fields.name: SPI_XTS_DESTINATION
fields.desc: This bit stores the destination parameter which will be used in manual encryption calculation. 0: flash(default), 1: psram(reserved). Only default value can be used.

fields.name: SPI_XTS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS
fields.desc: This bits stores the physical-address parameter which will be used in manual encryption calculation. This value should aligned with byte number decided by line-size parameter.

fields.name: SPI_XTS_TRIGGER
fields.desc: Set this bit to trigger the process of manual encryption calculation. This action should only be asserted when manual encryption status is 0. After this action, manual encryption status becomes 1. After calculation is done, manual encryption status becomes 2.

fields.name: SPI_XTS_RELEASE
fields.desc: Set this bit to release encrypted result to mspi. This action should only be asserted when manual encryption status is 2. After this action, manual encryption status will become 3.

fields.name: SPI_XTS_DESTROY
fields.desc: Set this bit to destroy encrypted result. This action should be asserted only when manual encryption status is 3. After this action, manual encryption status will become 0.

fields.name: SPI_XTS_STATE
fields.desc: This bits stores the status of manual encryption. 0: idle, 1: busy of encryption calculation, 2: encryption calculation is done but the encrypted result is invisible to mspi, 3: the encrypted result is visible to mspi.

fields.name: SPI_XTS_DATE
fields.desc: This bits stores the last modified-time of manual encryption feature.

fields.name: SPI_MMU_ITEM_CONTENT
fields.desc: MSPI-MMU item content

fields.name: SPI_MMU_ITEM_INDEX
fields.desc: MSPI-MMU item index

fields.name: SPI_MMU_MEM_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable mmu-memory clock force on

fields.name: SPI_MMU_MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to force mmu-memory powerdown

fields.name: SPI_MMU_MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: Set this bit to force mmu-memory powerup, in this case, the power should also be controlled by rtc.

fields.name: SPI_MMU_PAGE_SIZE
fields.desc: 0: Max page size , 1: Max page size/2 , 2: Max page size/4, 3: Max page size/8

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AUX_CTRL
fields.desc: MMU PSRAM aux control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RDN_ENA
fields.desc: ECO register enable bit

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RDN_RESULT
fields.desc: MSPI module clock domain and AXI clock domain ECO register result register

fields.name: SPI_CRYPT_SECURITY_LEVEL
fields.desc: Set the security level of spi mem cryption. 0: Shut off cryption DPA funtion. 1-7: The bigger the number is, the more secure the cryption is. (Note that the performance of cryption will decrease together with this number increasing)

fields.name: SPI_CRYPT_CALC_D_DPA_EN
fields.desc: Only available when SPI_CRYPT_SECURITY_LEVEL is not 0. 1: Enable DPA in the calculation that using key 1 or key 2. 0: Enable DPA only in the calculation that using key 1.

fields.name: SPI_CRYPT_DPA_SELECT_REGISTER
fields.desc: 1: MSPI XTS DPA clock gate is controlled by SPI_CRYPT_CALC_D_DPA_EN and SPI_CRYPT_SECURITY_LEVEL. 0: Controlled by efuse bits.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_REGISTERRND_ECO_HIGH
fields.desc: ECO high register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_REGISTERRND_ECO_LOW
fields.desc: ECO low register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DATE
fields.desc: SPI0 register version.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST
fields.desc: The current status of SPI1 master FSM.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST
fields.desc: The current status of SPI1 slave FSM: mspi_st. 0: idle state, 1: preparation state, 2: send command state, 3: send address state, 4: wait state, 5: read data state, 6:write data state, 7: done state, 8: read data end state.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PE
fields.desc: In user mode, it is set to indicate that program/erase operation will be triggered. The bit is combined with spi_mem_usr bit. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR
fields.desc: User define command enable.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_HPM
fields.desc: Drive Flash into high performance mode.  The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_RES
fields.desc: This bit combined with reg_resandres bit releases Flash from the power-down state or high performance mode and obtains the devices ID. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_DP
fields.desc: Drive Flash into power down.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_CE
fields.desc: Chip erase enable. Chip erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_BE
fields.desc: Block erase enable(32KB) .  Block erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_SE
fields.desc: Sector erase enable(4KB). Sector erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PP
fields.desc: Page program enable(1 byte ~256 bytes data to be programmed). Page program operation  will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done .1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_WRSR
fields.desc: Write status register enable.   Write status operation  will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_RDSR
fields.desc: Read status register-1.  Read status operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_RDID
fields.desc: Read JEDEC ID . Read ID command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_WRDI
fields.desc: Write flash disable. Write disable command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_WREN
fields.desc: Write flash enable.  Write enable command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_READ
fields.desc: Read flash enable. Read flash operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_VALUE
fields.desc: In user mode, it is the memory address. other then the bit0-bit23 is the memory address, the bit24-bit31 are the byte length of a transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_RIN
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of a MSPI read data transfer when accesses to flash, the signal level of SPI bus is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_WOUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of a MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the signal level of SPI bus is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during write-data phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during read-data phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during address phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FCS_CRC_EN
fields.desc: For SPI1,  initialize crc32 module before writing encrypted data to flash. Active low.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_TX_CRC_EN
fields.desc: For SPI1,  enable crc32 when writing encrypted data to flash. 1: enable 0:disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FASTRD_MODE
fields.desc: This bit enable the bits: spi_mem_fread_qio, spi_mem_fread_dio, spi_mem_fread_qout and spi_mem_fread_dout. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RESANDRES
fields.desc: The Device ID is read out to SPI_MEM_RD_STATUS register,  this bit combine with spi_mem_flash_res bit. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: SPI_MEM_D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WP
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WRSR_2B
fields.desc: two bytes data will be written to status register when it is set. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is alwasy on.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DLY_RES
fields.desc: After RES/DP/HPM command is sent, SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 512) SPI_CLK cycles.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SYNC_RESET
fields.desc: The FSM will be reset.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_mem_clkcnt_N.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_mem_clk. So spi_mem_clk frequency is system/(spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: reserved

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: the bit combined with spi_mem_mosi_delay_mode bits to set mosi signal delay mode.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FWRITE_DUAL
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 2 signals

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FWRITE_QUAD
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 4 signals

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FWRITE_DIO
fields.desc: In the write operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FWRITE_QIO
fields.desc: In the write operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MISO_HIGHPART
fields.desc: read-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_mem_w8~spi_mem_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MOSI_HIGHPART
fields.desc: write-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_mem_w8~spi_mem_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: SPI clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MOSI
fields.desc: This bit enable the write-data phase of an operation.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_MISO
fields.desc: This bit enable the read-data phase of an operation.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR
fields.desc: This bit enable the address phase of an operation.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND
fields.desc: This bit enable the command phase of an operation.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The length in spi_mem_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of  command.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1)

1610625060.name: SPI_MEM_MOSI_DLEN

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_QUAD

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WAITI_EN
fields.desc: 1: The hardware will wait idle after SE/PP/WRSR automatically, and hardware auto Suspend/Resume can be enabled. 0: The functions of hardware wait idle and auto Suspend/Resume are not supported.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WAITI_DUMMY
fields.desc: The dummy phase enable when wait flash idle (RDSR)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WAITI_ADDR_EN
fields.desc: 1: Output  address 0 in RDSR or read SUS command transfer. 0: Do not send out address in RDSR or read SUS command transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WAITI_ADDR_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: When SPI_MEM_WAITI_ADDR_EN is set, the  cycle length of sent out address is (SPI_MEM_WAITI_ADDR_CYCLELEN[1:0] + 1) SPI  bus clock cycles. It is not active when SPI_MEM_WAITI_ADDR_EN is cleared.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WAITI_CMD_2B
fields.desc: 1:The wait idle command bit length is 16. 0: The wait idle command bit length is 8.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WAITI_CMD
fields.desc: The command value to wait flash idle(RDSR).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER
fields.desc: program erase resume bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES
fields.desc: program erase suspend bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4 or *128) SPI_CLK cycles after program erase resume command is sent. 0: SPI1 does not wait after program erase resume command is sent.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4 or *128) SPI_CLK cycles after program erase suspend command is sent. 0: SPI1 does not wait after program erase suspend command is sent.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PES_PER_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable PES end triggers PER transfer option. If this bit is 0, application should send PER after PES is done.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable Auto-suspending function.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PESR_END_MSK
fields.desc: The mask value when check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit. If the read status value is status_in[15:0](only status_in[7:0] is valid when only one byte of data is read out, status_in[15:0] is valid when two bytes of data are read out), SUS/SUS1/SUS2 = status_in[15:0]^ SPI_MEM_PESR_END_MSK[15:0].

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_RD_SUS_2B
fields.desc: 1: Read two bytes when check flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit. 0:  Read one byte when check flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PER_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: Both WIP and SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits should be checked to insure the resume status of flash. 0: Only need to check WIP is 0.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PES_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: Both WIP and SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits should be checked to insure the suspend status of flash. 0: Only need to check WIP is 0.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SUS_TIMEOUT_CNT
fields.desc: When SPI1 checks SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits fail for SPI_MEM_SUS_TIMEOUT_CNT[6:0] times, it will be treated as check pass.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_COMMAND
fields.desc: Program/Erase suspend command.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND
fields.desc: Flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit read command. The command should be sent when SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit should be checked to insure the suspend or resume status of flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_SUS
fields.desc: The status of flash suspend, only used in SPI1.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_CMD_2B
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 sends out SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND[15:0] to check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit. 0: SPI1 sends out SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND[7:0] to check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_HPM_DLY_128
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_RES_DLY_128
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_DP_DLY_128
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_DLY_128
fields.desc: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_DLY_128
fields.desc: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SPI0_LOCK_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable SPI0 lock SPI0/1 arbiter option. 0: Disable it.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PESR_CMD_2B
fields.desc: 1: The bit length of Program/Erase Suspend/Resume command is 16. 0: The bit length of Program/Erase Suspend/Resume command is 8.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_COMMAND
fields.desc: Program/Erase resume command.

fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when Auto Resume command (0x7A) is sent and flash is resumed successfully. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.1: Triggered when Auto Suspend command (0x75) is sent and flash is suspended successfully. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when WRSR/PP/SE/BE/CE is sent and flash is already idle. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi1_slv_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. It means that SPI_CS raises high. 0: Others

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi1_mst_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered condition is that chip is loosing power and RTC module sends out brown out close flash request to SPI1. After SPI1 sends out suspend command to flash, this interrupt is triggered and MSPI returns to idle state. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_EN
fields.desc: 1: in ddr mode,  0 in sdr mode

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_VAR_DUMMY
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable variable dummy cycle in spi ddr mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_RDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder rx data of the word in spi ddr mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_WDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder tx data of the word in spi ddr mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_CMD_DIS
fields.desc: the bit is used to disable dual edge in command phase when ddr mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OUTMINBYTELEN
fields.desc: It is the minimum output data length in the panda device.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_USR_DDR_DQS_THD
fields.desc: The delay number of data strobe which from memory based on SPI clock.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP
fields.desc: 1: Do not need the input of SPI_DQS signal, SPI0 starts to receive data when spi0_slv_st is in SPI_MEM_DIN state. It is used when there is no SPI_DQS signal or SPI_DQS signal is not stable. 0: SPI0 starts to store data at the positive and negative edge of SPI_DQS.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the differential SPI_CLK#.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DQS_CA_IN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the input of SPI_DQS signal in SPI phases of CMD and ADDR.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_DUMMY_2X
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the vary dummy function in SPI HyperBus mode, when SPI0 accesses flash or SPI1 accesses flash or sram.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert SPI_DIFF when accesses to flash. .

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OCTA_RAM_ADDR
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable octa_ram address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[25:4], 6'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1], 1'b0}.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_CA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable HyperRAM address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[19:4], 13'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1]}.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_TIMING_CALI
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable timing auto-calibration for all reading operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: add extra dummy spi clock cycle length for spi clock calibration.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_EN
fields.desc: Register clock gate enable signal. 1: Enable. 0: Disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DATE
fields.desc: Version control register

fields.name: CONF_BITLEN
fields.desc: Define the APB cycles of  SPI_CONF state. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: UPDATE
fields.desc: Set this bit to synchronize SPI registers from APB clock domain into SPI module clock domain, which is only used in SPI master mode.

fields.name: USR
fields.desc: User define command enable.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable. Can not be changed by CONF_buf.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_VALUE
fields.desc: Address to slave. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DUMMY_OUT
fields.desc: 0: In the dummy phase, the FSPI bus signals are not output. 1: In the dummy phase, the FSPI bus signals are output. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: Apply 2 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_DUAL
fields.desc: Apply 2 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_OCT
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: HOLD_POL
fields.desc: SPI_HOLD output value when SPI is idle. 1: output high, 0: output low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: WP_POL
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: RD_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In read-data (MISO) phase 1: LSB first 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: WR_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In command address write-data (MOSI) phases 1: LSB firs 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_clkcnt_N. In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1). In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_clk. So spi_clk frequency is system/(spi_clkdiv_pre+1)/(spi_clkcnt_N+1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKDIV_PRE
fields.desc: In the master mode it is pre-divider of spi_clk.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: In the master mode 1: spi_clk is eqaul to system 0: spi_clk is divided from system clock. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DOUTDIN
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable full duplex communication. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: QPI_MODE
fields.desc: Both for master mode and slave mode. 1: spi controller is in QPI mode. 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: OPI_MODE
fields.desc: Just for master mode. 1: spi controller is in OPI mode (all in 8-b-m). 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: TSCK_I_EDGE
fields.desc: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of tsck. 0: tsck = spi_ck_i. 1:tsck = !spi_ck_i.

fields.name: CS_HOLD
fields.desc: spi cs keep low when spi is in  done  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_SETUP
fields.desc: spi cs is enable when spi is in  prepare  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: RSCK_I_EDGE
fields.desc: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of rsck. 0: rsck = !spi_ck_i. 1:rsck = spi_ck_i.

fields.name: CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: the bit combined with spi_mosi_delay_mode bits to set mosi signal delay mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_DUAL
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 2 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_QUAD
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_OCT
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 8 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_CONF_NXT
fields.desc: 1: Enable the DMA CONF phase of next seg-trans operation, which means seg-trans will continue. 0: The seg-trans will end after the current SPI seg-trans or this is not seg-trans mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: SIO
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable 3-line half duplex communication mosi and miso signals share the same pin. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MISO_HIGHPART
fields.desc: read-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MOSI_HIGHPART
fields.desc: write-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MOSI
fields.desc: This bit enable the write-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MISO
fields.desc: This bit enable the read-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_ADDR
fields.desc: This bit enable the address phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND
fields.desc: This bit enable the command phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The length in spi_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MST_WFULL_ERR_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

fields.name: CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles+1) of prepare phase by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_setup bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: delay cycles of cs pin by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_hold bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of  command. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MST_REMPTY_ERR_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

1611141148.name: MS_DLEN
1611141148.desc: SPI data bit length control register

fields.name: MS_DATA_BITLEN
fields.desc: The value of these bits is the configured SPI transmission data bit length in master mode DMA controlled transfer or CPU controlled transfer. The value is also the configured bit length in slave mode DMA RX controlled transfer. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS0_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS0 pin enable, 1: disable CS0, 0: spi_cs0 signal is from/to CS0 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS1_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS1 pin enable, 1: disable CS1, 0: spi_cs1 signal is from/to CS1 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS2_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS2 pin enable, 1: disable CS2, 0: spi_cs2 signal is from/to CS2 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS3_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS3 pin enable, 1: disable CS3, 0: spi_cs3 signal is from/to CS3 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS4_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS4 pin enable, 1: disable CS4, 0: spi_cs4 signal is from/to CS4 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS5_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS5 pin enable, 1: disable CS5, 0: spi_cs5 signal is from/to CS5 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CK_DIS
fields.desc: 1: spi clk out disable,  0: spi clk out enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MASTER_CS_POL
fields.desc: In the master mode the bits are the polarity of spi cs line, the value is equivalent to spi_cs ^ spi_master_cs_pol. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLK_DATA_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI master DTR mode is applied to SPI clk, data and spi_dqs.  0: SPI master DTR mode is  only applied to spi_dqs. This bit should be used with bit 17/18/19.

fields.name: DATA_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI clk and data of SPI_DOUT and SPI_DIN state are in DTR mode, including master 1/2/4/8-bm.  0:  SPI clk and data of SPI_DOUT and SPI_DIN state are in STR mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: ADDR_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_ADDR state are in DTR mode, including master 1/2/4/8-bm.  0:  SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_ADDR state are in STR mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CMD_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_CMD state are in DTR mode, including master 1/2/4/8-bm. 0:  SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_CMD state are in STR mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: SLAVE_CS_POL
fields.desc: spi slave input cs polarity select. 1: inv  0: not change. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DQS_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: The default value of spi_dqs. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CK_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: spi clk line is high when idle     0: spi clk line is low when idle. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
fields.desc: spi cs line keep low when the bit is set. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: QUAD_DIN_PIN_SWAP
fields.desc: 1: SPI quad input swap enable, swap FSPID with FSPIQ, swap FSPIWP with FSPIHD. 0:  spi quad input swap disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DMA_SLV_SEG_TRANS_EN

fields.name: SLV_RX_SEG_TRANS_CLR_EN

fields.name: SLV_TX_SEG_TRANS_CLR_EN
fields.desc: 1: spi_dma_outfifo_empty_vld is cleared by spi slave cmd 6. 0: spi_dma_outfifo_empty_vld is cleared by spi_trans_done.

fields.name: RX_EOF_EN
fields.desc: 1: spi_dma_inlink_eof is set when the number of dma pushed data bytes is equal to the value of spi_slv/mst_dma_rd_bytelen[19:0] in spi dma transition.  0: spi_dma_inlink_eof is set by spi_trans_done in non-seg-trans or spi_dma_seg_trans_done in seg-trans.

fields.name: DMA_INFIFO_FULL_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: 1: The current data rate of DMA Rx is smaller than that of SPI, which will lose the receive data.  0: Others.

fields.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_EMPTY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: 1: The current data rate of DMA TX is smaller than that of SPI. SPI will stop in master mode and send out all 0 in slave mode.  0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_EX_QPI_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI slave Ex_QPI interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Ex_QPI transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_EN_QPI_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI slave En_QPI interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode En_QPI transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_RD_DMA_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_RD_DMA_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Rd_DMA transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_WR_DMA_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_WR_DMA_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Wr_DMA transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_RD_BUF_DONE_INT_RAW

fields.name: TRANS_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_TRANS_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI master mode transmission is ended. 0: others.

fields.name: DMA_SEG_TRANS_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_DMA_SEG_TRANS_DONE_INT interrupt. 1:  spi master DMA full-duplex/half-duplex seg-conf-trans ends or slave half-duplex seg-trans ends. And data has been pushed to corresponding memory.  0:  seg-conf-trans or seg-trans is not ended or not occurred.

fields.name: SEG_MAGIC_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SEG_MAGIC_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: The magic value in CONF buffer is error in the DMA seg-conf-trans. 0: others.

fields.name: SLV_BUF_ADDR_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_BUF_ADDR_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: The accessing data address of the current SPI slave mode CPU controlled FD, Wr_BUF or Rd_BUF transmission is bigger than 63. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_CMD_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_CMD_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: The slave command value in the current SPI slave HD mode transmission is not supported. 0: Others.

fields.name: MST_RX_AFIFO_WFULL_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MST_RX_AFIFO_WFULL_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: There is a RX AFIFO write-full error when SPI inputs data in master mode. 0: Others.

fields.name: MST_TX_AFIFO_REMPTY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MST_TX_AFIFO_REMPTY_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: There is a TX BUF AFIFO read-empty error when SPI outputs data in master mode. 0: Others.

fields.desc: 1: reset, detection of a set reset mode bit results in aborting the current transmission/reception of a message and entering the reset mode. 0: normal, on the '1-to-0' transition of the reset mode bit, the TWAI controller returns to the operating mode.

fields.name: LISTEN_ONLY_MODE
