fields.name: SELF_TEST_MODE
fields.desc: 1: self test, in this mode a full node test is possible without any other active node on the bus using the self reception request command. The TWAI controller will perform a successful transmission, even if there is no acknowledge received. 0: normal, an acknowledge is required for successful transmission.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_MODE
fields.desc: 1:single, the single acceptance filter option is enabled (one filter with the length of 32 bit is active). 0:dual, the dual acceptance filter option is enabled (two filters, each with the length of 16 bit are active).

fields.name: TX_REQ
fields.desc: 1: present, a message shall be transmitted. 0: absent

fields.name: ABORT_TX
fields.desc: 1: present, if not already in progress, a pending transmission request is cancelled. 0: absent

fields.name: RELEASE_BUF
fields.desc: 1: released, the receive buffer, representing the message memory space in the RXFIFO is released. 0: no action

fields.name: CLEAR_DATA_OVERRUN
fields.desc: 1: clear, the data overrun status bit is cleared. 0: no action.

fields.name: SELF_RX_REQUEST
fields.desc: 1: present, a message shall be transmitted and received simultaneously. 0: absent.

fields.name: RX_BUF_ST
fields.desc: 1: full, one or more complete messages are available in the RXFIFO. 0: empty, no message is available

fields.name: OVERRUN
fields.desc: 1: overrun, a message was lost because there was not enough space for that message in the RXFIFO. 0: absent, no data overrun has occurred since the last clear data overrun command was given

fields.name: TX_BUF_ST
fields.desc: 1: released, the CPU may write a message into the transmit buffer. 0: locked, the CPU cannot access the transmit buffer, a message is either waiting for transmission or is in the process of being transmitted

fields.name: TRANSMISSION_COMPLETE
fields.desc: 1: complete, last requested transmission has been successfully completed. 0: incomplete, previously requested transmission is not yet completed

fields.name: RECEIVE
fields.desc: 1: receive, the TWAI controller is receiving a message. 0: idle

fields.name: TRANSMIT
fields.desc: 1: transmit, the TWAI controller is transmitting a message. 0: idle

fields.name: ERR
fields.desc: 1: error, at least one of the error counters has reached or exceeded the CPU warning limit defined by the Error Warning Limit Register (EWLR). 0: ok, both error counters are below the warning limit

fields.name: BUS_OFF_ST
fields.desc: 1: bus-off, the TWAI controller is not involved in bus activities. 0: bus-on, the TWAI controller is involved in bus activities

fields.name: MISS_ST
fields.desc: 1: current message is destroyed because of FIFO overflow.

fields.name: RECEIVE_INT_ST
fields.desc: 1: this bit is set while the receive FIFO is not empty and the RIE bit is set within the interrupt enable register. 0: reset

fields.name: TRANSMIT_INT_ST
fields.desc: 1: this bit is set whenever the transmit buffer status changes from '0-to-1' (released) and the TIE bit is set within the interrupt enable register. 0: reset

fields.name: ERR_WARNING_INT_ST
fields.desc: 1: this bit is set on every change (set and clear) of either the error status or bus status bits and the EIE bit is set within the interrupt enable register. 0: reset

fields.name: DATA_OVERRUN_INT_ST
fields.desc: 1: this bit is set on a '0-to-1' transition of the data overrun status bit and the DOIE bit is set within the interrupt enable register. 0: reset

fields.name: ERR_PASSIVE_INT_ST
fields.desc: 1: this bit is set whenever the TWAI controller has reached the error passive status (at least one error counter exceeds the protocol-defined level of 127) or if the TWAI controller is in the error passive status and enters the error active status again and the EPIE bit is set within the interrupt enable register. 0: reset

fields.name: ARBITRATION_LOST_INT_ST
fields.desc: 1: this bit is set when the TWAI controller lost the arbitration and becomes a receiver and the ALIE bit is set within the interrupt enable register. 0: reset

fields.name: BUS_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: 1: this bit is set when the TWAI controller detects an error on the TWAI-bus and the BEIE bit is set within the interrupt enable register. 0: reset

fields.name: IDLE_INT_ST
fields.desc: 1: this bit is set when the TWAI controller detects state of TWAI become IDLE and this interrupt enable bit is set within the interrupt enable register. 0: reset

fields.name: EXT_RECEIVE_INT_ENA
fields.desc: 1: enabled, when the receive buffer status is 'full' the TWAI controller requests the respective interrupt. 0: disable

fields.name: EXT_TRANSMIT_INT_ENA
fields.desc: 1: enabled, when a message has been successfully transmitted or the transmit buffer is accessible again (e.g. after an abort transmission command), the TWAI controller requests the respective interrupt. 0: disable

fields.name: EXT_ERR_WARNING_INT_ENA
fields.desc: 1: enabled, if the error or bus status change (see status register. Table 14), the TWAI controllerrequests the respective interrupt. 0: disable

fields.name: EXT_DATA_OVERRUN_INT_ENA
fields.desc: 1: enabled, if the data overrun status bit is set (see status register. Table 14), the TWAI controllerrequests the respective interrupt. 0: disable

fields.name: ERR_PASSIVE_INT_ENA
fields.desc: 1: enabled, if the error status of the TWAI controller changes from error active to error passive or vice versa, the respective interrupt is requested. 0: disable

fields.name: ARBITRATION_LOST_INT_ENA
fields.desc: 1: enabled, if the TWAI controller has lost arbitration, the respective interrupt is requested. 0: disable

fields.name: BUS_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: 1: enabled, if an bus error has been detected, the TWAI controller requests the respective interrupt. 0: disable

fields.name: IDLE_INT_ENA
fields.desc: 1: enabled, if state of TWAI become IDLE, the TWAI controller requests the respective interrupt. 0: disable

fields.name: BAUD_PRESC
fields.desc: The period of the TWAI system clock is programmable and determines the individual bit timing. Software has R/W permission in reset mode and RO permission in operation mode.

fields.name: SYNC_JUMP_WIDTH
fields.desc: The synchronization jump width defines the maximum number of clock cycles a bit period may be shortened or lengthened. Software has R/W permission in reset mode and RO in operation mode.

fields.name: TIME_SEG1
fields.desc: The number of clock cycles in TSEG1 per bit timing. Software has R/W permission in reset mode and RO in operation mode.

fields.name: TIME_SEG2
fields.desc: The number of clock cycles in TSEG2 per bit timing. Software has R/W permission in reset mode and RO in operation mode.

fields.name: TIME_SAMP
fields.desc: 1: triple, the bus is sampled three times. 0: single, the bus is sampled once. Software has R/W permission in reset mode and RO in operation mode.

fields.name: ARBITRATION_LOST_CAPTURE
fields.desc: This register contains information about the bit position of losing arbitration.

fields.name: ERR_CAPTURE_CODE_SEGMENT
fields.desc: This register contains information about the location of errors on the bus.

fields.name: ERR_CAPTURE_CODE_DIRECTION
fields.desc: 1: RX, error occurred during reception. 0: TX, error occurred during transmission.

fields.name: ERR_CAPTURE_CODE_TYPE
fields.desc: 00: bit error. 01: form error. 10:stuff error. 11:other type of error.

fields.name: ERR_WARNING_LIMIT
fields.desc: The threshold that trigger error warning interrupt when this interrupt is enabled. Software has R/W permission in reset mode and RO in operation mode.

fields.name: RX_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: The RX error counter register reflects the current value of the transmit error counter. Software has R/W permission in reset mode and RO in operation mode.

fields.name: TX_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: The TX error counter register reflects the current value of the transmit error counter. Software has R/W permission in reset mode and RO in operation mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_0
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 0 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 0 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 0.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_1
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 1 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 1 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 1.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_2
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 2 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 2 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 2.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_3
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 3 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 3 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 3.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_4
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 0 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 4 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 4.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_5
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 1 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 5 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 5.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_6
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 2 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 6 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 6.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_7
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 3 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 7 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 7.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_8
fields.desc: In reset mode, reserved with RO. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 8 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 8.

fields.name: DATA_9
fields.desc: In reset mode, reserved with RO. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 9 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 9.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_10
fields.desc: In reset mode, reserved with RO. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 10 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 10.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_11
fields.desc: In reset mode, reserved with RO. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 11 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 11.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_12
fields.desc: In reset mode, reserved with RO. In operation mode, when software initiate write operation, it is tx data register 12 and when software initiate read operation, it is rx data register 12.

fields.name: RX_MESSAGE_COUNTER
fields.desc: Reflects the number of messages available within the RXFIFO. The value is incremented with each receive event and decremented by the release receive buffer command.

fields.name: CD
fields.desc: These bits are used to define the frequency at the external CLKOUT pin.

fields.name: CLOCK_OFF
fields.desc: 1: Disable the external CLKOUT pin. 0: Enable the external CLKOUT pin. Software has R/W permission in reset mode and RO in operation mode.

fields.name: SW_STANDBY_EN
fields.desc: Enable standby pin.

fields.name: SW_STANDBY_CLR
fields.desc: Clear standby pin.

fields.name: HW_STANDBY_EN
fields.desc: Enable function that hardware control standby pin.

fields.name: STANDBY_WAIT_CNT
fields.desc: Configure the number of cycles before standby becomes high when TWAI_HW_STANDBY_EN is enabled.

fields.name: IDLE_INTR_CNT
fields.desc: Configure the number of cycles before triggering idle interrupt.

fields.name: RDN_ENA
fields.desc: Enable eco module.

fields.name: RDN_RESULT
fields.desc: Output of eco module.

fields.name: RXFIFO_RD_BYTE
fields.desc: UART 0 accesses FIFO via this register.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than what rxfifo_full_thrhd specifies.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the amount of data in Tx-FIFO is less than what txfifo_empty_thrhd specifies .

fields.name: PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a parity error in the data.

fields.name: FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a data frame error .

fields.name: RXFIFO_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than the FIFO can store.

fields.name: DSR_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of DSRn signal.

fields.name: CTS_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of CTSn signal.

fields.name: BRK_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a 0 after the stop bit.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TOUT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver takes more time than rx_tout_thrhd to receive a byte.

fields.name: SW_XON_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver recevies Xon char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: SW_XOFF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives Xoff char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: GLITCH_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a glitch in the middle of a start bit.

fields.name: TX_BRK_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter completes  sending  NULL characters after all data in Tx-FIFO are sent.

fields.name: TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has kept the shortest duration after sending the  last data.

fields.name: TX_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has send out all data in FIFO.

fields.name: RS485_PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a parity error from the echo of transmitter in rs485 mode.

fields.name: RS485_FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a data frame error from the echo of transmitter in rs485 mode.

fields.name: RS485_CLASH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when detects a clash between transmitter and receiver in rs485 mode.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the configured at_cmd char.

fields.name: WAKEUP_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when input rxd edge changes more times than what reg_active_threshold specifies in light sleeping mode.

fields.desc: This is the status bit for rxfifo_full_int_raw when rxfifo_full_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_INT_ST

fields.name: RXFIFO_TOUT_INT_ST

fields.name: SW_XON_INT_ST

fields.name: SW_XOFF_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for sw_xoff_int_raw when sw_xoff_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: GLITCH_DET_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for glitch_det_int_raw when glitch_det_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: TX_BRK_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for tx_brk_done_int_raw when tx_brk_done_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the stauts bit for tx_brk_idle_done_int_raw when tx_brk_idle_done_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: TX_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for tx_done_int_raw when tx_done_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: RS485_PARITY_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for rs485_parity_err_int_raw when rs485_parity_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: RS485_FRM_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for rs485_frm_err_int_raw when rs485_fm_err_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: RS485_CLASH_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for rs485_clash_int_raw when rs485_clash_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR_DET_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for at_cmd_det_int_raw when at_cmd_char_det_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: WAKEUP_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for uart_wakeup_int_raw when uart_wakeup_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: CLKDIV
fields.desc: The integral part of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: FRAG
fields.desc: The decimal part of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: GLITCH_FILT
fields.desc: when input pulse width is lower than this value the pulse is ignored.

fields.name: GLITCH_FILT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable Rx signal filter.

fields.name: RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Stores the byte number of valid data in Rx-FIFO.

fields.name: DSRN
fields.desc: The register represent the level value of the internal uart dsr signal.

fields.name: CTSN
fields.desc: This register represent the level value of the internal uart cts signal.

fields.name: RXD
fields.desc: This register represent the  level value of the internal uart rxd signal.

fields.name: TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Stores the byte number of data in Tx-FIFO.

fields.name: DTRN
fields.desc: This bit represents the level of the internal uart dtr signal.

fields.name: RTSN
fields.desc: This bit represents the level of the internal uart rts signal.

fields.name: TXD
fields.desc: This bit represents the  level of the internal uart txd signal.

fields.name: PARITY
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the parity check mode.

fields.name: PARITY_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable uart parity check.

fields.name: BIT_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to set the length of data.

fields.name: STOP_BIT_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to set the length of  stop bit.

fields.name: TXD_BRK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enbale transmitter to  send NULL when the process of sending data is done.

fields.name: IRDA_DPLX
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable IrDA loopback mode.

fields.name: IRDA_TX_EN
fields.desc: This is the start enable bit for IrDA transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_WCTL
fields.desc: 1'h1: The IrDA transmitter's 11th bit is the same as 10th bit. 1'h0: Set IrDA transmitter's 11th bit to 0.

fields.name: IRDA_TX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of  IrDA transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_RX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of IrDA receiver.

fields.name: LOOPBACK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable uart loopback test mode.

fields.name: TX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable flow control function for transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable IrDA protocol.

fields.name: RXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rxd signal.

fields.name: TXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart txd signal.

fields.name: DIS_RX_DAT_OVF
fields.desc: Disable UART Rx data overflow detect.

fields.name: ERR_WR_MASK
fields.desc: 1'h1: Receiver stops storing data into FIFO when data is wrong. 1'h0: Receiver stores the data even if the  received data is wrong.

fields.name: AUTOBAUD_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for detecting baudrate.

fields.name: MEM_CLK_EN
fields.desc: UART memory clock gate enable signal.

fields.name: SW_RTS
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software rts signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart receive-FIFO.

fields.name: TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart transmit-FIFO.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce rxfifo_full_int interrupt when receiver receives more data than this register value.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce txfifo_empty_int interrupt when the data amount in Tx-FIFO is less than this register value.

fields.name: CTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart cts signal.

fields.name: DSR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dsr signal.

fields.name: RTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rts signal.

fields.name: DTR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dtr signal.

fields.name: SW_DTR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software dtr signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum amount of data that can be received  when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: This is the flow enable bit for UART receiver.

fields.name: WK_CHAR1
fields.desc: This register restores the specified wake up char1 to wake up

fields.name: WK_CHAR2
fields.desc: This register restores the specified wake up char2 to wake up

fields.name: WK_CHAR3
fields.desc: This register restores the specified wake up char3 to wake up

fields.name: WK_CHAR4
fields.desc: This register restores the specified wake up char4 to wake up

fields.name: WK_CHAR0
fields.desc: This register restores the specified char0 to wake up

fields.name: ACTIVE_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: The uart is activated from light sleeping mode when the input rxd edge changes more times than this register value.

fields.name: RX_WAKE_UP_THRHD
fields.desc: In wake up mode 1 this field is used to set the received data number threshold to wake up chip.

fields.name: WK_CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to select number of wake up char.

fields.name: WK_CHAR_MASK
fields.desc: This register is used to mask  wake up char.

fields.name: WK_MODE_SEL
fields.desc: This register is used to select wake up mode. 0: RXD toggling to wake up. 1: received data number larger than

fields.name: XON_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xon flow control char.

fields.name: XOFF_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xoff flow control char.

fields.name: XON_XOFF_STILL_SEND
fields.desc: In software flow control mode, UART Tx is disabled once UART Rx receives XOFF. In this status, UART Tx can not transmit XOFF even the received data number is larger than UART_XOFF_THRESHOLD. Set this bit to enable UART Tx can transmit XON/XOFF when UART Tx is disabled.

fields.name: SW_FLOW_CON_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable software flow control. It is used with register sw_xon or sw_xoff.

fields.name: XONOFF_DEL
fields.desc: Set this bit to remove flow control char from the received data.

fields.name: FORCE_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the transmitter to go on sending data.

fields.name: FORCE_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the  transmitter from sending data.

fields.name: SEND_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xon char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: SEND_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xoff char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: XON_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is less than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1  it will send a Xon char.

fields.name: XOFF_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is more than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1  it will send a Xoff char.

fields.name: TX_BRK_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the number of 0 to be sent after the process of sending data is done. It is active when txd_brk is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_IDLE_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce frame end signal when receiver takes more time to receive one byte data than this register value.

fields.name: TX_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers.

fields.name: RS485_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to choose the rs485 mode.

fields.name: DL0_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: DL1_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: RS485TX_RX_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver could receive data when the transmitter is transmitting data in rs485 mode.

fields.name: RS485RXBY_TX_EN
fields.desc: 1'h1: enable rs485 transmitter to send data when rs485 receiver line is busy.

fields.name: RS485_RX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the receiver's internal data signal.

fields.name: RS485_TX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the transmitter's internal data signal.

fields.name: PRE_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first at_cmd is received by receiver.

fields.name: POST_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the last at_cmd and the next data.

fields.name: RX_GAP_TOUT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the at_cmd chars.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the content of at_cmd char.

fields.name: CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the num of continuous at_cmd chars received by receiver.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power down UART memory.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power up UART memory.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the enble bit for uart receiver's timeout function.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_FLOW_DIS
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop accumulating idle_cnt when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the threshold time that receiver takes to receive one byte. The rxfifo_tout_int interrupt will be trigger when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte with rx_tout_en set to 1.

1610612840.name: MEM_TX_STATUS
1610612840.desc: Tx-SRAM write and read offset address.

fields.name: TX_SRAM_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset write address in Tx-SRAM.

fields.name: TX_SRAM_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset read address in Tx-SRAM.

1610612844.name: MEM_RX_STATUS
1610612844.desc: Rx-SRAM write and read offset address.

fields.name: RX_SRAM_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset read address in RX-SRAM.

fields.name: RX_SRAM_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset write address in Rx-SRAM.

fields.name: ST_URX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of receiver.

fields.name: ST_UTX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of transmitter.

fields.name: POSEDGE_MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two positive edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

fields.name: NEGEDGE_MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two negative edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

1610612860.name: LOWPULSE
1610612860.desc: Autobaud minimum low pulse duration register

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the value of the minimum duration time of the low level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

1610612864.name: HIGHPULSE
1610612864.desc: Autobaud minimum high pulse duration register

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores  the value of the maxinum duration time for the high level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

fields.name: RXD_EDGE_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the count of rxd edge change. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_B
fields.desc: The  denominator of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_A
fields.desc: The numerator of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: The integral part of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: SCLK_SEL
fields.desc: UART clock source select. 1: 80Mhz.  2: 8Mhz.  3: XTAL.

fields.name: SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Tx/Rx clock.

fields.name: RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset UART Tx/Rx.

fields.name: TX_SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Tx clock.

fields.name: RX_SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Rx clock.

fields.name: TX_RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset UART Tx.

fields.name: RX_RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset UART Rx.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the version register.

fields.name: TX_AFIFO_FULL
fields.desc: Full signal of APB TX AFIFO.

fields.name: TX_AFIFO_EMPTY
fields.desc: Empty signal of APB TX AFIFO.

fields.name: RX_AFIFO_FULL
fields.desc: Full signal of APB RX AFIFO.

fields.name: RX_AFIFO_EMPTY
fields.desc: Empty signal of APB RX AFIFO.

fields.name: REG_UPDATE
fields.desc: Software write 1 would synchronize registers into UART Core clock domain and would be cleared by hardware after synchronization is done.

fields.name: ID
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the uart_id.

fields.name: TX_RST
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset decode state machine.

fields.name: RX_RST
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset encode state machine.

fields.name: UART0_CE
fields.desc: Set this bit to link up HCI and UART0.

fields.name: UART1_CE
fields.desc: Set this bit to link up HCI and UART1.

fields.name: SEPER_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to separate the data frame using a special char.

fields.name: HEAD_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to encode the data packet with a formatting header.

fields.name: CRC_REC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UHCI to receive the 16 bit CRC.

fields.name: UART_IDLE_EOF_EN
fields.desc: If this bit is set to 1 UHCI will end the payload receiving process when UART has been in idle state.

fields.name: LEN_EOF_EN
fields.desc: If this bit is set to 1 UHCI decoder receiving payload data is end when the receiving byte count has reached the specified value. The value is payload length indicated by UHCI packet header when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 1 or the value is configuration value when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 0. If this bit is set to 0 UHCI decoder receiving payload data is end when 0xc0 is received.

fields.name: ENCODE_CRC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable data integrity checking by appending a 16 bit CCITT-CRC to end of the payload.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1'b1: Force clock on for register. 1'b0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: UART_RX_BRK_EOF_EN
fields.desc: If this bit is set to 1 UHCI will end payload receive process when NULL frame is received by UART.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Indicates the raw interrupt of UHCI_RX_START_INT. Interrupt will be triggered when delimiter is sent successfully.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Indicates the raw interrupt of UHCI_TX_START_INT. Interrupt will be triggered when DMA detects delimiter.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Indicates the raw interrupt of UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT. Interrupt will be triggered when the required time of DMA receiving data  exceeds the configuration value.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Indicates the raw interrupt of UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT. Interrupt will be triggered when the required time of DMA reading RAM data  exceeds the configuration value.

fields.name: SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Indicates the raw interrupt of UHCI_SEND_S_REG_Q_INT. Interrupt will be triggered when UHCI sends short packet successfully with single_send mode.

fields.name: SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Indicates the raw interrupt of UHCI_SEND_A_REG_Q_INT. Interrupt will be triggered when UHCI sends short packet successfully with always_send mode.

fields.name: OUT_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Indicates the raw interrupt of UHCI_OUT_EOF_INT. Interrupt will be triggered when there are errors in EOF.

fields.name: APP_CTRL0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Indicates the raw interrupt of UHCI_APP_CTRL0_INT. Interrupt will be triggered when UHCI_APP_CTRL0_IN_SET is set to 1.

fields.name: APP_CTRL1_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Indicates the raw interrupt of UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT. Interrupt will be triggered when UHCI_APP_CTRL1_IN_SET is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_ST

fields.name: TX_START_INT_ST

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_ST

fields.name: APP_CTRL1_INT_ST

fields.name: TX_START_INT_ENA

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the interrupt of UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the interrupt of UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT.

fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the interrupt of UHCI_APP_CTRL0_INT.

fields.name: APP_CTRL1_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the interrupt of UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_RX_START_INT.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_CLR

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_CLR

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_CLR

fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_SEND_S_REG_Q_INT.

fields.name: SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_SEND_A_REG_Q_INT.

fields.name: OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_CLR

fields.name: APP_CTRL0_INT_CLR

fields.name: APP_CTRL1_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT.

fields.name: CHECK_SUM_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable head checksum check when receiving.

fields.name: CHECK_SEQ_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to  enable sequence number check when receiving.

fields.name: CRC_DISABLE
fields.desc: Set this bit to support CRC calculation, and data integrity check bit should 1.

fields.name: SAVE_HEAD
fields.desc: Set this bit to save data packet head when UHCI receive data.

fields.name: TX_CHECK_SUM_RE
fields.desc: Set this bit to encode data packet with checksum.

fields.name: TX_ACK_NUM_RE
fields.desc: Set this bit to encode data packet with ACK when reliable data packet is ready.

fields.name: WAIT_SW_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UHCI encoder transfer to ST_SW_WAIT status.

fields.name: SW_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to transmit data packet if UCHI_ENCODE_STATE is ST_SW_WAIT.

fields.name: RX_ERR_CAUSE
fields.desc: Indicates the error types when DMA receives the error frame. 3'b001: UHCI packet checksum error. 3'b010: UHCI packet sequence number error. 3'b011: UHCI packet CRC bit error. 3'b100: find 0xC0, but received packet is uncompleted. 3'b101: 0xC0 is not found, but received packet is completed. 3'b110: CRC check error.

fields.name: DECODE_STATE
fields.desc: Indicates UHCI decoder status.

fields.name: ENCODE_STATE

fields.name: TX_C0_ESC_EN

fields.name: TX_DB_ESC_EN

fields.name: TX_11_ESC_EN

fields.name: TX_13_ESC_EN

fields.name: RX_DB_ESC_EN

fields.name: RX_13_ESC_EN

fields.name: RXFIFO_TIMEOUT_SHIFT
fields.desc: Configures the maximum counter value.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TIMEOUT_ENA

fields.name: ACK_NUM

fields.name: LOAD

1610674176.name: EP1
1610674176.desc: FIFO access for the CDC-ACM data IN and OUT endpoints.

fields.name: RDWR_BYTE
fields.desc: Write and read byte data to/from UART Tx/Rx FIFO through this field. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_IN_EMPTY_INT is set, then user can write data (up to 64 bytes) into UART Tx FIFO. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT is set, user can check USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP1_WR_ADDR USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP0_RD_ADDR to know how many data is received, then read data from UART Rx FIFO.

1610674180.name: EP1_CONF
1610674180.desc: Configuration and control registers for the CDC-ACM FIFOs.

fields.name: WR_DONE
fields.desc: Set this bit to indicate writing byte data to UART Tx FIFO is done.

fields.name: SERIAL_IN_EP_DATA_FREE
fields.desc: 1'b1: Indicate UART Tx FIFO is not full and can write data into in. After writing USB_DEVICE_WR_DONE, this bit would be 0 until data in UART Tx FIFO is read by USB Host.

fields.name: SERIAL_OUT_EP_DATA_AVAIL
fields.desc: 1'b1: Indicate there is data in UART Rx FIFO.

fields.name: JTAG_IN_FLUSH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when flush cmd is received for IN endpoint 2 of JTAG.

fields.name: SOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when SOF frame is received.

fields.name: SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Serial Port OUT Endpoint received one packet.

fields.name: SERIAL_IN_EMPTY_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Serial Port IN Endpoint is empty.

fields.name: PID_ERR_INT_RAW

fields.name: CRC5_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when CRC5 error is detected.

fields.name: CRC16_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when CRC16 error is detected.

fields.name: STUFF_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when stuff error is detected.

fields.name: IN_TOKEN_REC_IN_EP1_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when IN token for IN endpoint 1 is received.

fields.name: USB_BUS_RESET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when usb bus reset is detected.

fields.name: OUT_EP1_ZERO_PAYLOAD_INT_RAW

fields.name: OUT_EP2_ZERO_PAYLOAD_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when OUT endpoint 2 received packet with zero palyload.

fields.name: RTS_CHG_INT_RAW

fields.name: DTR_CHG_INT_RAW

fields.name: SET_LINE_CODE_INT_RAW
